\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And I remember them putting pennies on her eyes, and we had those to spend. We - a penny. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she was a baby. I don't suppose she was a year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You don't remember the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I can't remember the funeral. I can remember my father dying, he died - I don't know the date.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 My name? Marg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
ret. Davies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Here? 9 Dean's Close, this is where I'll die I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Landuff, Cardiff, and you're a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - there's my husband. Gosh, I've got my certificate somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember the year? You were probably married in 1915, the year after the war broke out, and your year of birth, 1879?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In Bronant. Bronant, Cardiganshire. Mm. Near Aberystwyth. But I was only a baby in arms - coming from there you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you move then, from Bronant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 To Castle Street, Merthyr, and
 we lived there the whole time, in Castle Street - not quite opposite to where they've built - the New Castle Hotel, in Merthyr, you know it's by the Town Hall, so of course - we used to have all the fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 hts imaginable in that street, and we only had to go a short distance, we'd be in High - in Portmaldas you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long were you in that house then in Castle Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We lived in the house that we went first, it was rather a small house, and we lived there for about - I should think about ten year
s. And then we moved to a larger house, you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why did your father move from Bronant to Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well you see now my father was what you'd call - a carrier. A carrier. That means that he used to - bring - bacon, butter and eggs over - from Br
onant to Merthyr, and then his customers were up in Tredega, and all - round there you see, he'd a very good connection, and when they used to bring them over, they used to change horses, halfway you see. You know, for - for the horses to have rest, and -
 then my uncle - was a porthman, that means that he was buying cows - to send his son and daughter - to London. To Liverpool. To Liverpool. That - she was here Sunday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Porthman, it was a drover wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That's right. Very fine men, very
 tall they were, but of course you see my father - was so - kind you know, that they all used to meet, these carriers in the Crown Hotel at the bottom of the town, and of course they - we hadn't moved then you see. My mother was on the - on a little farm 
-
 that her father gave her, and she hadn't moved because we were a - crowd of - children, well - some were - were grown of course, and - what - where did I leave off - very kind, but you know, he used to spend money like water. Well of course my mother nee
d
ed it you see. But you know he was so - I had two sisters the same. You know, the same father and mother, but how they differed the children don't they. And - there was - my father - well Jane said she could remember - the - our cart full of golden sovere
igns, but you see my mother - was short of money, and she used to tell us - you can lift your head as high as anybody in Merthyr, I have never had parish relief. And she was so proud of that. But she was a wonderful woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your father was a carrier in Bronant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 With a horse and cart was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Horse and cart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why did he decide to move to Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course that was his - why did we - well because my mother could see - that there was no money coming back to the 
country you see, she - had to think of - living, and that's why she moved, or I don't suppose she'd have moved if my father - had - he was kind, but if he had only - used a bit of reason you know, because - he never missed Sunday school you know. But ther
e you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So then you were in the house in Castle Street then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, well now we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long were you there then in Castle Street, it was a little bit small you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you move then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We didn't move at all, we mo
ved to this - bigger house, because my - mother's started now - she could see - I think my father, no my father was alive - she bought a cow. And we had - two big cellars you see, so we could keep in one - the milk, and in the other the cow's feeds and - 
kept - the coal and everything in there you know. Well - then - my mother had to think now of - making a living, and she started by selling milk. And she worked from one cow until she had five. And you know, in those days - milk was only three}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ha'pence a pint. And she used to give us three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ha'pence, if somebody'd had a pint every day of the week, it would come to ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
pence ha'penny, she'd give us three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
ha'pence for her to have the whole shilling, not to change it. You see, there wasn't what they get today, the - the - for the first - for the second child you know. Nothing like that. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would your mother start keeping this cow now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well - we had a stable - no, in Merthyr. In the same Castle - now you see, we had a - a stable, at the 
back - we had to go round - to the stable, we couldn't go from our back door, and - my father had finished now with the carrying. He was doing nothing now. So we kept the cow there, then when we had more, we used to keep - there was room for about four I 
t
hink there, and then she used to have milk - from Cwm Taft. Do you know Cwn Taft? Do you? As you go to the Beatons. Well there were lots of farmers there, and they would bring milk down to - to us you see, because - ours wasn't enough to supply the custom
ers, she used to carry that milk - for - well I should think miles in the day. And Anne my sister was very good, she used to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother do this as soon as you moved from Bronant, or was it later on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - much later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you moved from Bronant to Castle Street, how many years were you in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We lived in the - in the first house, it was still in Castle Street, we lived there for about - eight years I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And then you moved to the bigger house in Castle Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Number ten Castle Street was the one you moved to, the bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why did they move there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well you see now Mary - was growing, and - we wanted more room. And of course we - you know - in between 
- the older ones were getting married you see, and - Mary and I were home, and Katherine, the youngest one. And - she - she - won a scholarship to the Higher Grade you see, the same time - as Lord Buckland. Have you heard of it. The same time as he, and W
illie was in my class in school. You see, well now they were - they - and there - there was another brother, of course today they're all Lords, there was another brother - th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 
at used to bring parcels up to yo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 u from Artie Jones' when we were doing the dressmaking, you know, so they started in a humble way you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh from Bronant. Cwrt Bach, that was the name of the farm he came from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And he was a carrier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he have any other job before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - do you know - my mother had the greatest difficulty - in trying to persuade him to go and do something. And she put a few shillings in his pocket, and she say - she'd say - tell him to go down to the sta
tion to see - if he could get a job to clean the - the - trucks or something. He would pay somebody to do that out of his - poor - what my mother went through. Nobody knows.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you moved to Merthyr the carrying job finished did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He still kept going back and forth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes, for a long time. But you see - there was no money coming in. I don't know, he was spending and spending, and - treating others you know. And - and I tell you an awful thing that I can remember so well. He we
nt a guarantor - for another man that was in business, but he was drinking. Do you know they came to - a bit of furniture we had, I can remember it now, they - taked it you know, because - we had no money to pay - for this guarantor, but my mother was hea
rtbroken. And she - sent to my uncle - in Liverpool - my Uncle John, her brother, a lovely man, and he came down and he said - oh don't fret Jane dear, he said, and he cleared that. But you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your father was generous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I can remember that event. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Terrible, I was only a little girl. And do you know we used to go to school to Abermorlais, to the same school as the Berry's went you know, and - all my friends you see were all - very nicely dressed, my part
icular friends, some of them lived in Castle Street, their father was a builder, but he was fond of his drink too, but they - had something at the back of them you see, and - but they always came to me to help with their homework. Now Mary passed, she had
 a scholarship, and of course if you didn't pass it was nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
pence a week you see. Well now my mother said - begged of me to go and try, but you know I was too proud because my friends - were going to pay, that I never tried. Well I'm sorry now. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Because it would have meant that you would have gone free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That's right. And they were all paying you see. But of course - Mary didn't trouble you see but I - I had that old pride you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your mother and father didn't make you try?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, but
 my father was so proud of Mary. And - she did well you know. But I tell you now - she went to the country with my father, my mother had this little place after her father, and her father said to her - Jane, if you - if you won't marry Richard, she said, 
I
'll leave you everything. But she married my father you see. And they were married on horseback you know. Yes. Yes. Well I can't - only what my mother used to say, they were not special horses. They were off the farm you know. And perhaps one of my - my g
r
andfather's farm, I never saw my grandfather, but Mary now used to go - would go with my father, she'd dress him - by her - mother would have - homespun cloth suit for him, dark grey, and he wore - these square hats you know, not a top hat, but a - and no
t
 a bowler. Yes. And he used to look very smart. But you know now - he'd come back without a ha'penny. Not a ha'penny. It was a - it wasn't a big farm. Isn't it strange. One of their members - in Treherbert, lived in that farm. When my mother owned it you 
know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he drink, is that why the money went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh yes, and treating them in the - in the - Three Horseshoe in - and then poor old Mary you see, my mother thinks - that she had a - a damp bed, and she had an abcess on her face, and on her arm he
re, and here. And of course our Mary was very proud you know, although - she wanted to be a scholar, but she had to give it up you know, although - she wanted to be a scholar, but she had to give it up you know because of her health, and she started - sew
i
ng. And do you know she was only eleven, I think she was eleven when my father died. She made all our bit of mourning. She'd never had a - a trade. And she never used a pattern. She was - wonderful at designing, but no good at sewing. So that's where I ca
me in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She would do all the cutting out and designing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And seeing the customers. And I'll tell you another thing, do you know there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  Davies' - dressmakers, and who do you think they were? You know this - Attenborough is his name? His - 
his mother-in-law's - mother and her sister. They lived in Twyn Rhodyn, but of course - we had a huge - business. Well - three of our shops - asked us if we would take over their - their business you know, but we had too many customers of our own. Mind, w
e were not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 har}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ing like they do today. Do you know what we were charging for a costume? A pound. A pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Father didn't really have any other job, only as a carrier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well he - he tried to go to the station but he never did anything. No. He was k
ind enough if you can understand, but - the drink had taken hold of him you know. It was such an extent that you felt so sorry for him. I can't even remember - my little youngest sister - being born you know. Nor Catherine, I can't remember them being bor
n.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You remember your father out of work a lot then do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You remember your father being out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - oh, I - I never remember him working after he gave up the business. But he'd go with my mother now - if she was going 
to Brecon fair, to buy a cow, he would go with her you know. And I remember another tragedy - the cows were not far - from where my sister's husband - designed houses, isn't it strange? And we went up one - day to milk, we went with her, and there - the c
ow had been drinking - stagnant water, and it was dead. And - ill - she could ill afford - to lose her. Twice that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So really your mother kept you going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - she was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She was working really when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Just by keeping this cow, milking it, and selling the milk and then she'd have five cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Yes. And then we'd - if - if - we'd have milk from the farms then you see. Oh dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was it only your mother then ran the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, Anne would help her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That was your older sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Now she - not - not the oldest. Now by this time - Liza the eldest one had got married you see. She went - she went when we moved to Merthyr, she went to my uncle. Uncle John, my 
mother's brother, to Liverpool, and Ellen went to my father's sister - in London. But Liza didn't stay long you know. And she came back - and my mother gave - them all a trade, but - but they didn't stick to it you know. One day my mother was going down a
n
d she saw Jane, she was a terrible girl Jane. She saw Jane - cleaning the windows - in - the Temple of Fashion - workroom - cleaning the windows, and - all she'd made there were watch pockets. And then she had a sweetheart and - I can remember another inc
ident - I - Jane - Ellen and Anne were courting, and they were bringing their sweethearts to have tea one Sunday. All preparations. And my mother said - have you been to Sunday school? No. You shouldn't bring those boys in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They couldn't come because they hadn't been to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 'Cos they hadn't been to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did they think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, they were shocked but they would never answer back. The children today you know, it's - it's all foreign to me today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So your mother worked really all the time did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh she worked - she worked and she - built a - a semi-detached villa, she called it Bronant. And she built a house in - Brunswick Street. All out of - her - her earnings you know and her savings. But you know - I 
wouldn't change the way I've been brought up, isn't it strange. Because - I think it forms character don't you? You know - because - there was no need for it mind. But there you are. Well I suppose -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You couldn't help it though could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. An
d then my eldest sister - she made the biggest mistake of her life. She married a fellow by the name of Arthur Morgan. He had a very nice butchers shop. But - he again was fond of drink. And poor Liza, she worked - and she was the quietest of us, she was 
t
he eldest of all. She worked, and it was a pleasure to see her - behind that counter, so clean - and I - and it was a flourishing trade you know, but there's a man again that spent two fortunes. And poor old Liza you know - often times she came home, and 
s
he said, oh mammy, she said, I can never live with Arthur, and she'd had two children but they both died. And my mother used to say, oh Lisa dear, try your best, you know, 'cos he - it was nothing for him to have a knife - and - would - wouldn't mind - ki
lling her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They don't know what they are doing do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well then - poor old Arthur died. There was a lot of kindness in him again, you know, when he'd be all right he'd take her out in the gig you know, and - he was great on these shows, taking 
the horse and cart - to show, and - and the judge - the judge gave him - second prize and he called the judge - he told the - judge to wipe his arse with it. That's the type he was you see. But she became a widow, and - she had such a nice time now, 'cos 
s
he still had the business. The owners of the shop would never look at Arthur. It was always Mrs Morgan, she had to take their orders you know, they'd come in their horse and trap you know, and they'd - buy - a side of - of lamb and things like that you kn
o
w to put in - they didn't have cold storage then, but they'd put it in a cold - 'cos they lived in - big houses you know. Yes. And - old Arthur - old - Sam Dicks now, he was a cab proprietor, and he had an hotel. And his wife had died and he'd a houseful 
o
f children. And - he started going back and forth to Georgetown, after my sister you know. She was quiet type. And my mother - she'd come to chapel Sunday morning, she'd call in Castle Street, on the way back, and my mother used to say, Lisa dear leave th
a
t old man alone. She used to beg of her. She didn't listen see. But he got married, and he only wanted a woman for one thing, and do you know what that is? And she said on her deathbed - that she would rather live with Arthur - in a - in a cottage, than w
ith Sam Dicks in a palace. Now see if she'd only listened to my mother. So we've had a lot of - ups and downs you know. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you were children and your mother was busy with her business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who looked after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well 
I think we looked after ourselves. And my father was very good now - I can always remember - he would toast bread for us, and butter it, and he would put - sweet tea over it you know, that - my daughter was telling me they do that in the north now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Like sop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Mm. Well of course he didn't have the money then to spend you see. But he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He was looking after you really, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - and the - the older ones you know until they got married you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about life at home now in Castle Street, up to the time when you left school, can you remember the house, how many rooms were in it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I can remember - the front had a - a big window, with I don't know how many panes, and we were growing now and we were a bit ashamed
 of the old front of the house you know. Because our friends were nice you know. And we were very friendly with the owner of the house. So we used to tell him - oh I can't bear that old window, indeed they altered it for us, well that was our front room. 
W
e had a big kitchen. Spotlessly clean I may tell you. And then we had two cellars. Big rooms and steps to go down. Then - we had two bedrooms, and on top of that another two - on top of that, an attic. So - so you see, when Mary started now - with the dre
s
smaking, the girls had the back bedroom, you know. And then - I had to go up after finishing, I had to do all the chores you know, the - for my mother. I had to go up to the - other - one of the other rooms, with about three girls you see, because - if th
e inspector came and found too many in the workroom we could have been summoned you see. 'Cos they were very particular then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live in the house? Were there any other people living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - no. My brother - my brother - well of course, when he came - the only brother - when he came from Cardiganshire you see, he hadn't had a lot of education. And he was too old really to go to a - a - to the Abermorlais where we went, so
 my mother had - she was a member in our chapel, to come in to give him lessons you know. And he - and two others - they - they went as coachmen - to - some of the doctors in town, 'cos in those days doctors were doctors you know. And - they had more fun 
o
ut of it because they had to wear - wear uniform you know. Well they didn't stick it long anyway, but John got a - a job - in the signal box, as a signalman. And he worked himself up from there - he - they sent him to - Aberdylis and dear me - Mary and I 
used to go down to the station to fetch his washing you know, it would come by train, and - there'd be always - a three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
penny bit each for us you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You liked going down to the station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And - of course, we all thought there was no one like John. He was the only boy. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So it was only your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh my father died you see, my father died. How old - well Mary was only about eleven when my father died you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So you were only about nine and a half years old when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So you do remember your father living at home with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes good gracious yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he do anything in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he do any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he wash up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. Well - you see, we were - all now - more or less capable, because Anne was home and she was a good girl you know. And Jane would be home. And then they met - they met their sweethearts later you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about improvements to the house or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh well the - the - I forget what rent we were paying. I don't think it was - nothing like you hear today. Oh - Ivor Davies the owner - would see to that. We didn't bother him much though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your father ever dress you or undress you when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. I'm glad you've asked me that. On a holiday - he would - we had - we - this is the time when we had the horse and cart. He would put us in the cart - and take us up and where do you think he used to 
land us? Do you know Kevan at all? The cemetery's that side, and the Kevan hotel is this side. We were planted in this cemetery while he went to the Kevan Hotel. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was he like when it came time to take you home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we had a dog, Julia, the dog knew every public house. Isn't it awful. And yet I loved my father see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would happen when you were coming back from the trip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I don't know, we were very - we were very happy 'cos we were having a ride in the cart. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you realize that your father was drinking when you were little?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh very hurt. Mm. And I can remember you know when he died, he had - these - delirious tremens you call it? I can rememb
er that, you see, he was almost an alcoholic wasn't he? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there much suffering with it in the home because of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - my mother - she had overcome it you know. Do you know, when she came - from Bron and she couldn't speak English you s
ee, and she didn't know the difference, people used to come to the house - for duck eggs, and hen eggs, she didn't know the difference between duck eggs and hen eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But - but she had got then you see - to - well we could help her a - a little, she had got then to - read the Echo before she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
In English. In English, and I can remember - I can remember some Englishman coming to our door and - must have been taken short, and you know all the toilets w
ere in a row. Beautifully clean mind. And - they were - opposite our back door. Have I told you this before? And he - he wanted to go to the toilet, my mother told him, yes, yes, she said, the first little house. I can always say you know - that we had cl
eanliness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You said your mother overcame it, your father's drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh she - she had got - she had - when now - when all the girls - had got married now, she was nice in a comfortable position you know, and I was the last home you see. And - do 
you know it used to give me such pleasure - now on a Sunday my mother would go - Mary and I would dress her you know in a - make her a lovely cape, and - a little bonnet, I used to make the bonnet for her, and - I've got a photo of her, would you like to 
s
ee it? And - well in fact - when my sister died now about two years or three years ago, she had the Sunday school class - then I should - well - well look Peggy, I said, to her daughter, don't destroy that because I would like to have that. Mm. But you kn
ow they don't hang them up today like - like we used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It's nice to look at them isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. And - it used to give us such pleasure - her to look nice and she'd have her bonnet, and a little bit of white silk, you know, tied here - round her
 neck, and she'd go to chapel and do you know - I used to enjoy making a nice dinner for her by the time she came home. Oh and she - she used to appreciate that, but - you know, things change don't they, after I got married - my brother you know - he made
 
a big mistake again you see. My sister died, that kept the butchers shop and John - and she'd a shop in Kevan as well, and John thought now, he's getting tired of the - station, and he was an inspector, on the - on the platform you know. A nice position. 
And - he made up his mind that he was going to - take Liza's business over. Well he got friendly - you know this Mr Jones, now he's the head - of the - what do you call this board where the people come -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you say she was too proud to have it, why do you think they were too proud to have the old age pension?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well, she - she thought it was something like the - parish relief you know. That's how she felt. But I think she had it for about a year. Before she died. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think they felt like that about the parish relief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, you see - why what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think they felt like that about the parish relief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh my mother was very much against it, she thought it was - you know - I don't know, what she - well - it was onl
y the very poor that went for it you see. But look at them today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother ever have to go for it? Did she ever have to apply for relief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was the washing done at home, or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - I can tell you - no - my mother and I did the washing. I'm thinking now when the girls had got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you were a little girl, before that, when you were still in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well, Anne now - Anne would help her then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 One of the older girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. But you know, this is our - the routine for washing. Two waters before they are boiled. Wash them again the tub, and then - throw them into - cold water until the water is
 clear. The work - and do you know it's no wonder my mother used to tell me - you are sure to be destroyed, she used to say, 'cos I used to wet my feet you know. And look at my hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Rheumatism isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't get pain but I think it - I
 - you know, I've - I've worked through all my life. And hard - and it - you know you get - now Nina gets a woman in here. They don't put weight in it like they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They used to really clean everything didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - spotless clean. And bake our own bread you see and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh dear, well you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you were children when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. I can remember - oh I never forget this too. I can rememb
er Nellie and I going to chapel on the Sunday morning, and we'd had new frocks, and my mother had them made - that she wouldn't have to - lengthen them at all they were nearly down to our ankles. And there was a - friend of ours - Martin Evans, he was a s
olicitor afterwards, and his sister Emily, I could tell you a lot about - we used to go and send them down the bottom of the town, and we thought - with these - long dresses that we were it, but I'm sure we looked sights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But they were new frocks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, she had a little woman - living - not far from where we kept our cows, and she would make them and - they didn't charge as much you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your mother wouldn't make any or mend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, but you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would she mend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I tell 
you she was always knitting. You know, not - mind I remember her knitting some nice Jaeger things for our children, but I had to do the - shaping you see, but she would do the knitting. And she would knit socks, you know - stockings, white stockings, we u
s
ed to say - she was like the circus girl going to bed, because she'd have these white stockings on, and then she'd have a flannel petticoat you know, oh dear and we used to laugh. But she was very humorous. Mm. Full of humour. Yes. And they tell me that w
h
en she - came to Merthyr she was a very good looking woman. She was fair, with beautiful features, we had my father's features. And - lovely blue eyes and a - a rosy colouring you know. And of course her teeth were good but she said - the water in Merthyr
 - spoilt her teeth, so she didn't have any teeth, she did - wouldn't have false teeth. No. Well I don't know, are you -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have new clothes or would they be second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 hand?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd never have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 hand. No. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would they be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we'd - my mother would buy the material and have them made you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would she buy the material?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11014482\charrsid7633169 Oh in - where the Manche}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ster House.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, and the Temple of Fashion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh nothing like they get today. You - when we needed them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about shoes, would you have new shoes or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you buy the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd go - mind - I think we often had them that they 
were not fitting. Not properly. As they should - as they should - as they are today you know. I know - Nina and Tudor - they - well of course everything's so changed isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you say they were not fitting, did you mean you didn't go to the shop yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We went to the shop but we didn't trouble whether they pinched us or not because they were new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would you have new clothes - new shoes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well when we needed them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any jobs you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father when you were a little girl in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did I what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any little jobs you had to carry out in the house regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, but - but after I got to an age - I sort of - took control, isn't
 it funny. When I was very young. You know, now Mary wasn't much of a cook you see. Mary Catherine and I - were the last - like to be together you see. And - it used to give me such pleasure - to try everything you know. A gadget, if there was a gadget go
ing - I'd have to pay for it myself, out of what I'd saved you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you were still in school? Would you have any little jobs to do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your brother and sisters? What about the older sisters and brother, would they have little jobs to do regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well my - my mother put the girls to sew. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But - and - and - and a bit of brass we had - but you know - we used to scrub - the tables you know. We had a 
- a round table, and a square table, they were scrubbed; regularly. And - it would be nothing to see - perhaps five of us - sitting round the little white table having food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember how you sat for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well round this little round table, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you sit, would you have the same places always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, not particular - I think my father and mother would, but I - my father - my father - gone now you see, it - he was out of it altogether.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He wasn't having meals with you really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well he was dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when he was alive? Do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh he took his part as a - as a farther, I can remem - my mother must have been in bed - having one of the children you see, and he - was seeing to our food then. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember one of the children being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I - I can't remember them being born, but I can remember, I told you little Sarah, when she died. And - of course we were not - we were - you know, the - the - they put pennies on her eyes and they gave them to us to spend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You remember your father looking after you when your mother was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would he do, would he look after you completely? Or would somebody else come in to help him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well - you know - we - we used to help - help one another, more or less. I don't think we depended much on my father you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would the older children help the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 To dress and everything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - oh yes. Mind I had to do my homework, and Katie Williams always came - now she was - that builder's daughter, she'd always come and ask me to help her with her homework. 
And we'd be in the front room and we could see my father coming up, and if she saw my father coming - he was - very straight but he was swaying, she'd be out through the back door like a shot. She was afraid but there was no need for her to have been afra
id you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. Mind I - as I grew older I used to think - what a difference it - it would have been. Wouldn't it you know - because we could have been so - comfortable, but mind - my mother lived to see us all comfortably - situat
ed. Which is - considering. Oh yes, considering - what - she had very nice - nephews that used to come to see her. Well they talked to my mother - just as if they were brothers and sisters because - these are Uncle John's - family from - one was a decorat
or in Ynysabul, the other - was a builder, and he had a son - an architect, they - they were all such nice boys you know. That's on my mother's side now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And they would visit would they a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How often would they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
On a Saturday as a rule. And - they never called her auntie you know, Jane always. And she al - they - my mother then was able to give them such a nice welcome you know. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your mother put you to bed when you were a little girl or anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I can never remember my mother putting us to bed. We - we had to - more or less - do for ourselves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you share the bedroom with anybody, or bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - Mary and I slept together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In the same bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And my mother and - Auntie Kit, in the other - the - it was a biggish room, and we had two beds there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember when you were children what the sleeping arrangements of the family was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I can tell you that we had - what
ever we had on the bed it was clean. But we didn't have - eiderdowns or anything like that you see. Nothing. You - you know, I - I can remember them - more in their own homes really. Do you see. They probably would have - that's why do doubt - that we mov
ed from - from the smaller house, because of the bedrooms you see. But you see after they got married - Mary had - two workrooms you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you were children how would you all sleep then? You and Mary were in one bedroom were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. We'd never - I've - I - I don't know now - whether there wasn't one at the foot of our bed. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So there were two beds in your room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And a little bed, three beds probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Auntie Kit - Auntie Kit - Catherine was sleep - with my mother 
you know, 'cos she was a bit spoilt, and then the others would sleep upstairs you know. When they were younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - down the cellar. In a tub. And I tell Lisa often you know - they put this old - stuff in the water to
 wash their hair. Do you know my mother would put - a hadful of soda in the water, and we had the loveliest heads of hair - shining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It is now isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well it was dark then. And it was down to here. And - a pleasure to see our heads. And my mo
ther was very particular - to use the small toothcomb you know. Because - you know in school there was some very dirty children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was it like then in Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - we had tramcars you know, going up, and - I can remember the - first cinema
 being built. And my mother said - the Devil's work. The Devils' work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, regularly. Not - Lisa baths nearly every night - once a week. And once a week I bath now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - whenever - whenever we bathed we'd have clean clothes you know, perhaps - not grand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any occasions when you'd eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only - only when our girls had some visitors they'd go to the front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they have a meal in the other room then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you know, isn't it strange now, I can never remember my mother cooking. It was either one of us always. Because she had - she had other -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You don't remember what sort of cooking equipment it was? Was it a range, a coal range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no. We didn't even have a gas cooker. Anoven. And - mind we used to take the bread to the bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 house. You see, and our - Christmas pudding - Christmas cake would go to the bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 house. No, no, none of the facilities we've got today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - we'd have to be in school you see fairly early. Oh round about eight o'clock. 'Cos we'd have porridge 
first. And - I - I never remember bacon for breakfast. Never. Toast. And of course - we didn't eat the fruit that we're eating today either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you have to drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh tea. But I remember - our - after - there was a shop in M
erthyr Gunsons, one of our best shops, and we used to go down there - for a quarter a pound of coffee and they'd grind it, you know - while you wait and the smell was beautiful. And my mother had got very fond of coffee. You know, occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What members of the family were present for breakfast, when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I think - I think it was more in relays then anything else. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your mother have breakfast with you or would she be up earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she - she would - she'd have 
to go - in the summer now she'd have to go up to the field to milk the cow you see, and one of us - if there was no school, we would go with her you know, and it was a long way to walk, and carrying all that old - milk back you know. It was hard work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She knew how to look after cows didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So your mother would be out early would she, she wouldn't have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She'd have it before she went. And if Anne went with her you see, they would both have it you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - do you know I can't remember much about him because he - he would be - when he was with his business he'd be off early you know. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, I suppose he would I - I can't rememb
er much about that. I know we - we were never - we were never short of - good plain food. Thank goodness for that. We never saw - you know, some are very - well perhaps there's no method to I don't know. We always had very good - plain food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you have for midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - broth chiefly. Broth. And of course you see, meat - in those days - wasn't nearly as expensive as it is today. And of course - I'm going back now - when - we were more flourishing, and Liza had a butchers shop, and we
 were always having nice piece of meat you know. To - do whatever we wanted to with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have a main meal dinner hour, would you have tea then or would you have an evening meal, when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh tea, and then have - something for supper, perhaps bread and milk or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about at the weekends? Would you have different food on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd have a nice - a nice Sunday dinner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You said your mother baked her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Every time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would she bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. We did all that. You see - that's before the time - that was during the war chiefly wasn't it. Well I used to do all that. Bottle tomatoes, bottle everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But when you were children would anybody do it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your mother make pickles, or wine, or medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was any beer br}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
wed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, we didn't have a garden. Although mind I can remember my father - that he did have some sort of a garden at the top - but oh I don't remember much about him. About it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they buy vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. You know - if the money was to be spared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about tinned vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Not - not when we were small. But when - say now when I was - able to do things you know, I used to do all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you were children in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you keep any livestock for the family? You said you did keep cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Goats?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 'Cos you see we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You're talking now - my sis
ter that lived in the country, they had - two goats you know. Of course they were - in a flourishing position 'cos he kept a shop, and they had a - a carbach, and the pump was out there you know, and I used to go there when the children were born, and sta
y about five weeks. And then Mary was writing - when you coming home, because it was a loss to her you see. But of course I was pleasing my mother - by going to the girl's. When the children came you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever have extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Rabbit? They wouldn't touch it. No. But mind - when I was in the country my brother-in-law would shoot a rabbit you know, but - we were never str - it used to make - Mary very ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many times a week did you eat meat while you were as little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I think most - most of our meals then were - was broth you see. So there would be meat - in the broth and we would have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your father have more food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well he'd have what he wanted you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We had to eat what was given us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was your parents attitude -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Without grumbling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I don't think there was any - uneaten unless it was Mary. She was the - she was the fidget. Now I've gone very fidgety now at my age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But when you were children what would happen if Mary left it on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh nothing. Well I expect the dog would have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had a dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We had a dog, and we had a lovely old cat. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt would you ask someone to pass}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 it to you or would you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I - I expect we'd grab it when we wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - if we wanted it you know, if there was some there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you expected to hold a knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never been taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you expected to sit in a certain way at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, but we were not allowed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could you bring toys to the table, or books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you mean when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Having food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When could you leave the table after a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 As soon as we'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The - all that would be in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How was the meal served, would your mother serve it all out or would she put it in tureens or would she serve it from the saucepans?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he, she'd se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 rve it on plate you know. No tu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 reens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would she serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I except my father you see 'cos she - she had great respect for him you know because - I think they were true lovers you know. But you see - she must have been disappointed. And he used to go to Sunday school and one of our
 deacons - on the Sunday, and his class - where he was - they were - in the big seat you know, and old Little Morgan the butcher we used to call him, he said to my father, this is no place for you today you know, he said. After where you were yest - last 
night. My father never want there afterwards. But you know - that the - his - all the Sunday school would come down to our house, and they would discuss - there, on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They must have been fond of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? Yes. Well they would discuss because he was - he had quite a good head on him you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Only to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And he stopped going there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And - do you know, it's a funny thing, but Morgan's the butcher, the family, nothing great
 came out of them you see. Well I tell you, Bessie married - Tom Price the musicians son, and Maggie Jones Hope you know, Mrs - what's her name that you - Mrs - you know - happy family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did the younger sisters sit before they could feed themselves? There was only Catherine and Sarah you'd remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh little Sarah died - in - in - when she was a - a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Catherine, you wouldn't remember because there wasn't much between you was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. She was more spoilt t
han I was though. 'Cos you see, the older girls were able to give - and help now when you are married, and they would give Catherine music lessons, not that she ever did anything with it, and she was like my father in a way. She would give and give and gi
v
e. But she would - if she was short - of a bedspread or something - she'd come and ask me you know for it. You see, what's the good of giving if you go without, and now her son - is in this home in Dowdas you know. He's - mind - poor old Nina, she says to
 him, Glyn, what if you come down to us for a week or a fortnight. Well we couldn't manage him. Because you see - they -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She could be very charming but she was very strict. Very strict. With us you know
. But - she'd - she had mellowed you know, she was eighty-six when she died you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we had to behave ourselves. We had to behave ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. She - I think she was very proud of us you know. Well we - not one of us had - gave her trouble before we were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Yes. I loved my mother. She was wonderful. Oh yes, you could share and tell her
 everything. Mind - she - she was terrible when we were courting. If you're in - if you are doing office work she used to say - lady's hands, she used to call those. And old tall boy she used to call mine. And - she never encouraged sweethearts. Isn't it 
strange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I don't know. She never encouraged them into the hose. But at the end mind, my husband used to come but my mother had gone to bed, and I'd have to tell him to go. I was the last you see getting married. And of course -
 we nearly all met our husbands in chapel apart from Liza, and Ellen. Now Ellen married a - a farmer, and - she had gone over to Liza you see before she was married, and that's where she met her husband. And that farm was called Twyn Cotga, well she - poo
r
 old Mary used to say when they used to ask her, how many children does Ellen had? Well there's so many living and I don't know how many she's had in liquid form. Mary used to say. Oh dear, but mind - she - she brought up quite a nice family - nearly all 
retired, the - Harold and Louis were in the bank, isn't it strange, all our boys went to the bank and all our girls did dome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
tic science. Mm. And one of her daughters had - she had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh ch
arming. Charming to a - to the - to his pals you know. And very nice to my mother. I can always remember her calling him Richard you know. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he show you affection, your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - in a very - masterly way you know. You know, we had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ehave, and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If you had any worries could you share them with your father or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh respectful, I would - I would never answer my mother back. Never. Not one of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - I don't think that we used to - dada we used to call him you know, I don't think that - we used to talk a lot to him. It was all my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brother and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, but - we had - perhaps we'd have a free fight. You know, when you're a lot of children, you - you're only two girls. But - we had two tubs in one cellar you know this is the cellar where we used 
to wash, and there was a bench there, and we - we had - a tub with water and we'd keep the milk - 'cos there was no - now - nowhere to put - freeze it you know, to keep it cool, and the milk wasn't there but I remember Jane and I had a - and she threw me 
in the tub of water. But we were best of pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
s afterwards. And do you know, that oak table that's in the passage, I'd grown now of course, and there was no - leg, there was a - a centre leg, but there was no - nothing else, and I thought to myself - I've a g
ood mind to take the top of that table to - the country school, there was evening - classes, and I'll carve the top of it. And there was an old man living in - not far from Castle Street, he was lame, but a wonderful craftsman, and do you know he's made t
hree beautiful - oak - you may see it, it's in the passage. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did your parents say if another child hurt you, did they tell you to hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We had to fight out own - we never - we never brought - any of our worries in to them, bec
ause - if - you know - we were a crowd of children, and we'd have our own fun, and Jane was a terrible girl and there was a - an auctioneer living the top of the street - and they were a big family, eight or nine you know, and old Alec, the son, he was an
 auctioneer too, the - after he had grown, and we'd have a slide from the top of the street to the bottom, and - Jane and Alec would be - in the front, and they'd leave us go you see and down we'd go. Oh dear, we had a lot of fun too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you allowed to get dirty when you went out to play?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 To get dirty? Well I can't remember - getting dirty you know, like you see some children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, my mother taught us - to 
go to chapel regularly you know. And - I think that she was quite satisfied at the end. She was worried about Liza mind. Very worried. And she didn't like Ellen's husband much. But she never interfered. Then - Catherine lost her husband you see, when - be
fore he was forty. Now he was a very clever accountant - in Guest Keene and Nettlefold's in Dowlas, very clever boy, and he died, he had pneumonia, and - Glyn is the only one left you see, this boy, and he's a wonderful mathematician.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well they brought us up to be truthful. That's a certainty. And to be honest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well do you know now, I never remember my father swearing. Strange isn't it? Never remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen? Would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If you did something that your parents disapproved of, what would happen, would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I think if we did anything like that we wouldn't show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember ever being punished for doing something naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I'll tell you how my mother would punish us. She'd 
give a good tug to our hair. Yes. That's how she'd punish us. But I never remember having - an awful whipping or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You don't remember really a particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't. But I can remember - I al -
 often think of poor old Nina. She was collecting for the - missionary, you know, the card. And she and another girl spent a penny you know. Oh - I gave her the finest whipping - I don't think she will ever forget it. And that's the only time I remember p
unishing Nina.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever have to punish your son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. Poor old Tudor, he swears that I used to put him - well you'd think you know - he - he swears that I put him to wash the scullery. Oh Nina was a very good little girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you say t
hat you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Say today now - think I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course at the
 end you see my mother played - the most important part, but - my father was - you know, he - we shouldn't do anything that wasn't right with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not a scrap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Anybody to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not when we were small mind. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, but I remember - I remember - when my father was alive, it would always be a goose. And of course we were not so struck on geese you see. We preferred a turkey. Always a goose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He liked a goose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Margie's the same. Tudor's wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you cook the turkey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 On a jack you know. And turn it round. It was beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had a fire in the cellar did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh huge, we used to boil the clothes down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You wouldn't cook anything down there though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh n
o. On - only in front you know, there was no oven. I'll tell you - my mother was never - after we'd got on - there was always one or two tons of coal, well of course it was much cheaper and - and it was coal. Always had plenty of - these old sleepers you 
know, John used to be able to get those - pay - a small fee. And when we - then we used to have them - sawn you know. Always had a stock of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any musical instruments in the house when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We had a piano, but mind - it was Mary bought the piano you know. But she never learnt. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh nothing. Band of Hope. And recite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there anybody in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, my mother had quite a nice voice, when she was younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. I don't think we were a - I - I wouldn't say that we were a musical family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we had - Thomas Charles Commentary, and all those heavy books you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Only the Marthyr Express, we used to take - I can't remember - and the Echo at the end. But before that I don't - oh and - the Cwmbr
w and - those Welsh papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Cerhadar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Not - no - with the - with the Presbyterians.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Goseuad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Goleuad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Those were the only magazines really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No magazines. When we were small. But mind we made up for it - it's when w
e were small you really want to know? I'll tell you what - what - what I can remember as we were growing up, the Queen died you know, the old Queen Victoria. And - girls of my age you know we all went into mourning and my mother was laughing, because we w
ent into mourning after the Queen you know. Yes. All -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Black, really, deep mourning. I'm laugh - my mother used to laugh about it because - now - we were very friendly with the owner of our - we were very friendly with the 
owner of our house you know, and she was a smart girl, she was in mourning and there was old - another architect, he's got a ni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
ce - living here, fond of the drink again he was, belonging to the Ratcliffes, Cardiff you know, and - I - and Mabel, she went with - a crowd of us went into deep mourning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But you had mourning in the house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we didn't buy it. No. You know, we managed to - fake something up for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Reading? Oh my father was a great reader. He used to read a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well at the end you know she used to read - she'd read the Echo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you were children? She could read Welsh could she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She couldn't read English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But she never - she never had time to read to us. But isn't it strange, we got on well in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did they ever read aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did they read to each other, would your father read to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I remember my father of course. And I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was his funeral like, can you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, you know - they didn't - no. Just - ordinary and a lot of his friends came, but no cars or anything like
 that. Walking you know most of the way. Up to Kevan. Of course it's going back. Because I remember - when - when we had a car first - we took my mother for a run, and she thought it was good for rheumatism. We took her to the country to where my sister l
ived. She thought it would cure her rheumatism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your father's funeral, would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I don't - no, I don't remember going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 None of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. I can't remember my mother going either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who attended it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would come to the funeral, your father's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who? Well his Sunday school class would be there you see. And - some of his pals. Plenty of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about mourning clothes, do you remember wearing mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - mourning you say? Well Mary made - Mary made them. After - after - after a fashion you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you taken out visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Bu
t we had plenty of friends - to play with. And - people from my mother's - class in Sunday school - used to visit us, but she didn't have a lot of time you see for visitors. Because she was more or less - the breadwinner you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And of course she had no relations did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. But if people came from the country you know, they would always - did I tell you - one old gent said - in Welsh, I'll say it in English shall I? Where does Jane Davies the widow live? When he got to the station. When he go
t to Merthyr station. He said - where does Jane Davies the widow live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he find her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he find her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. He did. Well you see, Merthyr in those days - there were no factories, like today. You know, we knew everybody. And of c
ourse - the doctors, well they were almost like little gods you know in those days. And of course no tram cars, no - no - cars, just - the carriage and pair, and their coachmen, and - well they thought they were it you see. And the solicitors the same. Bu
t today you see it's all changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I can remember - that we had to do the bit of shopping, you know, the shops were so near - to where we lived, that we only just go round the corner and we'd have what we wanted. Becau
se, later you see - my mother always kept - a sack of flour in the house, later you know. We were never short of food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you went out shopping with whom would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, perhaps - my sister. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Some of them were quite a bit older than you weren't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, I was the youngest but one. The youngest but one alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Did you ever go out with just your father, you told me about the trip to the cemetery, did you ever go out with him otherwise? With just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. But you know - with all his - like - that was his fault, was drink. Nothing else. He wasn't a nasty man. But - his smile was wonderful. I - you know, he used to show his teeth. And - give a broad smile, but - we never sort of - like I was reading tod
ay about Jeremy Thorpe and his little boy, what a lovable father he is. Well there was nothing like that about my father. But we had to behave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He wouldn't show you affection you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No. Must have shown tremendous lot to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember any outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I can't remember. Because - if we would go for a little outings, we would go - a crowd of us together, and I'll never forget - I can remember this - vividly you know. There was a - cemetery - we lived 
in Castle Street, and you went up a hill and that was Thomas Street, and there was a cemetery - there - I think it was called the church cemetery, and - three or four of us went up you know, and we could see - it's ridiculous when you think of it, 'cos we
 
could have been poisoned, we could see these gold - you know the golden chains - and - they're like - kidney beans. Well - Cassie Price - she lived - she lived about three doors from us, and my sister older than me and myself, we started eating these. And
 
we came back, and we were very sick. And Mrs-Price, she kept a public house and they kept cows, and of course my father used to go there a lot you see. And - Mrs Price said - are the girls all right? 'Cos they knew we'd been with Cassie. No, my mother sai
d, they have are very bad up the - we were sick you know, we could have been poisoned. Now see we were son innocent - that we didn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You don't remember going on any outings on Bank Holidays with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. Only - when we got older of course we went to our - Sunday school outings, you know, to Dolga and Llangors, and those pretty little places round the - still there, very pretty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You'd go with the Sunday school outing would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - round about August.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever go away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I didn't. When I was a child. But my sister went with my father. To the country to - Cwtbach, that was his ho
me do you see. And - she - I told you didn't I that she came back and she had a damp bed. And - he'd come back, he didn't have a panny of the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You never went away yourself? You don't remember any of the others going away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not whe
n they were small. 'Cos you see - Liza and Ellen - were - one was in London with my Aunt Jane, and - the other was with my uncle, my mother's - brother. I Liverpool, until they grew up a bit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you spend Saturdays in those days, while you were still at school? What would you do on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh, we'd go - a crowd of us would go round the market, and do you know innocent little fun like that, nothing outstanding. Not like today you know. Things have changed haven't they? Well of course, 
you see, you can't say that we were - very affluent - in those days. 'Course things are different today aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh chapel. Chapel in the morning. Sunday school and chapel at night. And then when we got older we used to g
o for walks. After chapel. Up - where they've built houses now, everywhere. You know, it was a - more of a lover's walk you see, it was - going out to the country, and we'd go mind - for or five of us would go for a nice walk, we were too small then to ha
ve sweethearts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You girls would go together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 m. Girls. But we nearly all - met our husband's in chapel you know. Mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were mixing with them weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were mixing with them you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have different clothes to put on on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we had our Sunday clothes you know, I told you about that long frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, you know, child - not - anything like they play today. But I used to hear my mother saying - that w
hen she was in the country - they used to play - she called it bando. Now I - what is that equivalent to - to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It's something like rounders isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I think - is it? Rounders or - I don't know, but they used to play I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you play any games when you were little,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only skipping and - tops and all that sort of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Very much, now I knit now on Sunday. My mother - would think it was dreadful. But I
 don't think myself - if your thoughts are nice - do you think it's wrong? You don't? All - safer then. But mind - it wasn't wise to go out in the dark because - there used to be terrible fights you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You couldn't go out in the dark?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we
 were afraid because - there was so many fights - on the street you know, and you see Castle Street - was between the main street - and what they call - well the - the worst part of Merthyr, where the iron bridge was, and where the - prostitutes were you 
know, and a lot of people - common, drinking and - fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would be fighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would be fighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh men, you see, perhaps they'd have an argument, and they'd - perhaps they'd be in the public house having an argument 
and they'd come in the street, and there'd be a crowd round them watching them, no one stopping them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was frightening. Really frightening. You don't see that today do you? At least -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So you wouldn't go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh no. Never. Never. And once we started school you see - we had our homework, and - we were quite - my sister - Mary was bright, but Jane - she was terrible in school. You know, she'd - she never tried - but - her - a really nice nature, an
d plenty of friends always. Oh the schools were so different then - to what they - mind, you know there was discipline you see. How much of this is going down anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents think it wrong for you to play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Hardly - we only went to chapel you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - well - regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Calv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
nistic Methodist then of course. Presbyter -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Both of them the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How often would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 My mother would go - usually in the afternoon to Sunday school, but - of - later year she would go the three times you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well she'd go in the afternoon and in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Sunday school he would go you see, until - that little - deacon insulted him, and then he didn't go afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He wouldn't go in the morning or night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You went the three times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mentioned there were Sunday school outings, what other social activities organised by the chapel did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well of course - Band of Hope was a great thing you know. And I remember - a little fellow by the name of Dick Toska - a very ardent member in Port M
orlais, and he used - to say - he never called me Getta, but Greta, Greta, he said, I want you to learn this, he said, and I'll take - we'll go up to Pendaren to a public house and I'd have to recite - Old tree, how old - how low you seem to stoop, how mu
ch your trunk is bent, I can't remember much more, but I used to recite that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you go to the public house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, he - he had it in the long room you know. Oh a crowd of us, the Band of Hope would go. Because that was Dick Toska's - his life you
 know. He was a short little man, and I think he did something underground. But - the family were members. The girls of course one was a teacher, and Maggie was at home, and I - I wish I knew now one of their relatives married only about a month ago, a ve
r
y - she was a Merthyr girl originally, but she's in some high school here, she was a widow - I think she got married, and - her husband - she left her husband for some reason or other, and - she had a - I'll tell you who was telling me all this, one of th
e -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Only the Band of Hope was it that you took part in in chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
And - Good Templars. There used to be a meeting, and in Port Morlais you know 'cos of course - Port Morlais was a huge chapel, and we had a little vestry, and you know we used to h
ave the regalias and it was all hush hush. I expect your husband perhaps would remember would he? Oh you had to give the password before you could go in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was a temperance thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Good Temperance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there a choir, did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - later on - E.T. Davies came - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there a choir in the chapel there, were there many activities with the choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The choir when you were in chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - now - yes, well I wasn't so little. Of course we used to have little singing schools in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 Band of Hope, and we used to re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 tire. But - when E.T. was our organist - he came from Gyfava church to Port Morlais you see, 'cos he was really a Methodist, a Calv}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 nistic, and - he was wonderful with -
 with our choir - with our choir you know, we sat in the gallery, the men and the women, and - he taught us to sing properly you know. And it was really very very good. And it's very strange, my ni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ce's husband took Gyfava then. He was a schoolmaster in Merthyr. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 E.T. Davies was very talented wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh very. Yes. Yes. Mind we used to pay him - how - how did they used to say now? It was over a pound a Sunday and we couldn't really afford it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mentioned that you were in the temperance, in the Band of Hope, was there any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - later you see - the young people would have a soiree. And - one of our little deacons, that one that spoke to my father, he - kicked up such a row, you think -
 that a soiree - was a terrible thing you know, in those days. And we didn't have it in the chapel or in the schoolroom, we had it - in an old - in a building where the Salvation Army used to be. That's where the soiree was. Well we had a lovely time. But
 - there was no dancing or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - talk and - you know, we'd have musical chairs or - little - innocent things like that you know. There was no harm in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, we didn't. But they did - they did in the country you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I - I d
on't - I don't know. He used to spend a lot of his time with the little man that kept - we used to call him - David, Cheese and Butter, but he was somebody in the town. He was a council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 or you know, and a very educated man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What were his politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
And then they would talk about the council - meetings to my father, 'cos he used to spend - a lot of his time there, so he must have been interested, but I never heard much of it at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What politics was this David Cheese and Butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well he was a great Liberal. Liberals they were in Merthyr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What do you think your father was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I think my father was a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think he would be a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know. You see, we had Pritchard Morgan - he came out as a Li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 b}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
eral and D.A. Thomas. And - and I remember them - I remember the - the lections very well. Oh - mm? Well - we had torchlight you know, going round the streets, and - crowd walking behind, and it was - folks -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was that little ditty you were saying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well you know Folks Griffitsh was a - a Tory, and we used to sing, we'll hang Folks Griffiths on a sour apple tree, and that would go on and on and on, and then - Pritchard Morgan, Pritchard Morgan, Pritchard Morgan this time, this time Pri
tchard Morgan, Pritchard Morgan this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He was the Liberal was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Liberal. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you sing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh on the street. In the - in the - processions. But I can remember this vividly, I was older now mind - Keir Hardy starte
d coming to Merthyr you see, a big socialist, and - and a very good man. And - you've heard me talking about - Lord Buckland, well there was a huge meeting in Soer chapel right opposite our chapel, the two biggest chapels in Merthyr. There was a huge meet
i
ng there, and - see whose coming out now, as a candidate you see, he - I think he was coming out as a - a - either an Independent or a Tory, I don't think he was Liberal, I'm not sure. Well anyhow - they wouldn't give him a chance to talk, and he had done
 quite a lot in Merthyr you know. You know, he had improved several things, well his monument is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
front of the library. Well - they wouldn't give him a chance, you know, the - these - these - Socialists were so strong that they were being and all the re
st of it. Well the - the - the meeting finished and we were coming out now and I was with my sister and a few of us, and I said well I think - I said, I think the least thing they could have given him a chance to talk. Oh, if I did. Do you know that there
 was - they were running after us, we got so frightened that we - that we got on a - a bus from Merhyr to Dowlas you know, there was a bus, we got on that we were so frightened, 'cos they were really }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 laggards}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 . Mind, I think it's a good thing in a way that t
hey - that they are - you know - we've - we've received a lot haven't we since, but - I don't know, there's - something very cheap about them too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 People were intolerant then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Oh they were terrible. Terrible. Mind you, I knew that many tha
t we were friendly, well my - I've got - a book there when - when my - well now there's a lot of the councillors there, and some of them are very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your mother, would she have any views on politics when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She was all - she - well she would vote Liberal you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think she'd vote Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I suppose it's - because - I think, I don't think that she knew - a lot about it - because her father and mother were Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was Cardiganshire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. That's what I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I couldn't vote then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Women didn't have the vote did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Oh I'm sure - I'm sure they would vote. I can't go back that 
much, but Tudor was telling me on Sunday - that - well he said, you know, mam you remember - you remember the - horses and carts going up and down the high street, well he said, you must have seen a lot of horse manure about the place. Well, I said, I was
n
't looking for that sort of stuff, and he was - he thought - that would be - very interesting 'cos you don't see so much today do you. See it was all horse and carts and - a gig you know, I remember my sister and her husband going - they had a gig but of 
course he was an awful man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would there be many horses and carts and gigs, were people well off enough to have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well you see - you see - well a tradesman, my brother-in-law was, but his love was horses and carts, and - people had got on in 
business, they would have a trap you see because - there was such lovely - runs up to Cwmtaft you know. Mm -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had stables in your house didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No - it wasn't - it wasn't attached. We had to pay rent for that. It was round the back you se
e. And - it was our stable - but we could keep - four cows in it. And do you know, the way my mother used to clean - that - and she'd come in after milking, she would change everything. In case - the customers could smell manure. She was so particular. Bu
t oh she worked hard. But she - she was very happy. And I never - I never remember - my father and mother quarrelling. Never, and gosh she had plenty of room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their jobs if they voted differently from their employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well now I - I wouldn't be surprised - that during that time you know, there was that element.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your father wasn't working was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No. He was a freelance you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was he a member of a political party, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember him working for one of the parties at an election,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she wouldn't work - she wouldn't work for them. She would vote and that's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. The only thing I can remember - my father was very keen - on education you know, at that time. And of course - he was so thrilled - that Mary had passed the higher gr
ade, and no doubt - she - she would have made a wonderful writer you know. She had she had a lot of - of - what's the word I want? Not intelligence. Yes. And of course it - you see she - it turned out - that she showed it. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - we had a - we had what they call a skew in the kitchen. My father would sit there, and have a 
smoke. And perhaps my mother would be mending then. That's how they would spend their time. Or my father perhaps would read you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think she did. Her chapel was her - all, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh very rarely. Very rare - rarely. She was glad to be home you see after milking, taking the milk out you know. Oh - and you see - everything had to be so - spotlessly clean. Because you - you had to be
 very careful, dear dear, I met a - I don't want this to go down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many evenings a week would your father spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh dear. I don't like to say this. I can't remember him - I can't remember him ever spending - an evening at home. He'd c
ome home perhaps - well he'd come home in the daylight, so he must have been sitting - there some where. No, it's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He didn't come home from work because he didn't have any work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But he'd come home and - this little friend of mine would be i
n our front room. She - she - but you see we'd see my father, and he was very tall and straight, but he'd be swaggering a little bit see. And we'd know that he'd had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Pubs, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But not clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And he'd go every night really would he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Well you know, spend more - I don't know, perhaps he'd meet some of his friends, I don't know, we never used to question him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your mother ever go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I 
can't - the only time I can remember my mother - she wanted a cow - and they went I think it was to Brecon or Hereford. They wanted to buy a cow. And my father went with her. And that was the last time he was out. And - my sister Anne then - there were th
r
ee - three were two between us, Anne was third up, and - Anne would be scrubbing the - we had a big table in the kitchen, and a little round one, and she'd be scrubbing those, and do you know, in her hurry like - she - she put the little table on top of t
h
e other, and a piece about that width - came off. She didn't know what to do but there was this - Williams the builder at the back of our house, he had a workshop. So we went for him. But this is the part - she was courting now and she wanted a new hat se
e. And she was rather on the shy side. So she said to me, Geta, she said, go up to the house and - ask if you can bring a few hats, 'cos you could have them on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 apron}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  in those days. So I went up and there was a navy flock you know, and she had rather a biggi
sh face. And I - I said this is nice on. And it suited her you know. And she said, what'll I have on it? Asking me that was - about - six or eight years younger than her. Well I don't know, I said - I'd like a little bit of something red, it was a navy - 
a
nd it was a smooth felt you know. And there was a tiny little - it wasn't an osprey, a pretty little thing, for the front - for the side of the hat. She said, do you think - it was red, do you think that'll be nice, she said to me. I said, yes, I do. So -
 my mother came home - and my father never went out after see. And my mother said when she saw the red in the hat, red is unlucky. And my father died soon after. I found my certificate. Do you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Only the - Sunday school. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They had a savings club did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters, before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh, all right. You know - brothers and sisters, you don't know what it is to be a - big family do you? You know, we'd quarrel and then we'd be the best of friends. No one else would have to say a word between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I was very fond of my eldest sister. I - I slept with her when she was a widow. For about two years you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That's Liza?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Lisa. I was very fond of her, and - she was another quiet one you see but - she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169  - she married two - well horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  men. And I - used to think - she'd make a lovely minister's wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - all the - we - the - do you know, the - the families in our street, there was Lewis the auctioneer, they were ten, Williams's the b}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ilder, now Katie was my great friend, of course she was dressed much nicer than I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you notice that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I did. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you feel it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Very much. Very much. An
d now Catherine my youngest sister, she was able to have nice - pinafores you know because - the older ones - could buy them for her you see, and give her music lessons but she didn't make anything of them, she was more of a spoilt girl although she was o
nly - two years younger, it's her son we visit now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever say anything to your mother about it, that you felt you were dressed differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. I never used to. But I used to call for Katie - in the morning because we were only a few doors
, and Mrs Williams was a very nice woman, very refined, but they had a lot of trouble, the boys - were nearly all drinking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there a lot of drinking in Merthyr then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I should think there was, because - Mrs Williams herself was a perfect little lady, and I called for Katie, and she'd say - Marg}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 aret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
, have a bun, you know, home made bun she'd make, and of course they had a big - kitchen built on you see, but the father went bankrupt twice you see. So she had her share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who did you play with mainly, the children in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
With Katie. Although mind - oh dear dear, she seemed to be - much more grown up than I was you know. You know, she would - she used to frighten me a bit. Mm. I don't want this to go down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She was your best friend really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
She was my - biggest friends, you know, we would walk down - we'd walk down from school, it was a tip you know and we used to walk down - from school and she was always beautifully turned out and a very good looking girl, but 
she died of cancer. She got married you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you play with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you play when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we'd either play - out the back you see, because - there was a row of houses, and a - big
gish back you see, we could go there, and then - in our house - we could go down the steps - and there was a square piece down the bottom, that we could play out the back, or - on the street, or - on our steps. You know - that was the fashion then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go to other children homes to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never hardly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What games did you play, you mentioned skipping and top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Top. Now what else - oh and skate, you know we used to - the slides in the winter. We used to enjoy those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, mother - they didn't - she wasn't particular about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know, we seemed to - do you know now - it's a funny thing, but - my sister Mary an
d I, we were nearer one another's age, and really we - had more in common as we grew, but you know we used to be very particular who we'd choose our friends you know. You know, we always sort of - hitched our wagon to a star as it were. You know, we - alt
h
ough mind - you can say that we were not - well you could say we were poor in a way, but - we never mixed with an old sort. And - and even - even when we grew older - we were very particular, I - I - I always think - much more particular - than these two 
girls are today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think you were like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I'm wondering - whether it's - was pride or what.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 interfered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So it wasn't that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I can't remember anything like that in Merthyr you see at that time. When we were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Now how would you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I can't remember, play mostly I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You said you had homework in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Lots of girls used to collect wild flowers and press them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we used to go out you know and - and of course - there would be an exhibition - f
or wild flowers and we used to go up - out in the country you know and pick - beautiful bunches - bunches of these - of these wild flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would the exhibition be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh it would be in connection with the - Market Square, that's an English Independent. Where Seymour Berry was a member. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You'd collect these flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And we would put them in - you know, comp - for competition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you do anything else, did you keep any pets? You mentioned you had a dog and a cat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh
 a lovely - and a cat. Oh my mother - used to talk to the cat, and do you know that she went - she was milking the cows, she had a nice singing voice, she used to sing when she was milking, and she used to say that the - cows gave more milk. Mm. Yes. Well
 she used to sing to them. And she used to talk to them exactly as if they were human beings. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever do anything with the cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Never. I went to visit my sister - Llwyn Groes, near Lampeter, near Llangeitho, they kept a shop there, 
and they had one cow for their own use you know, and they had it in the - cabach they called it, and - have I told you this before? And - Anne was going to chapel and of course it - she always milked. So she said to me - I said, look, Anne, I think I coul
d
 milk you know, I said to her. And - well all right, she said, try. I - I went when they went to chapel, I took the bucket - and the stool, and I was there when they were coming out and I hadn't had a drop of milk. And - Miss Williams - they kept a farm c
a
lled Penbuwlch, another lovely woman, and she said - well, Gretta dear, what are you trying to do, she said to me. Trying to milk, I said to her. Oh leave it to me, and she milked the cow. Well - this Sally was telling me - when she was here - that she ne
ver attempted to milk, and her mother used to tell her - you are very hard. Too much like work. And she couldn't milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You never tried when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no, no. Perhaps my mother would let us - I - you know, at the end. And perhaps we'd have a little drop then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. My father did start - having a garden, it was a long way off. And I can remember him bringing things down from this garden to - but I think he used to spend most of his time in the publics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You'd go for walks?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Plenty of walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We - we would walk - oh - gosh. I remember - a friend - friend of mine - we went for a run on bicycles, this was older now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I should think I'd be about - fourteen or fifteen. And we went for this - we went a long way you know, and - I think we must have lost our way. Well she was a grocer's daughter. And - and we're coming back now. Oh 
we had been miles out of the way. We came back - and do you know that it was getting - very dark, what's happened? Well am I giving you - anything? Oh and my mother was worried because - no sign of me coming home. And I - I - I don't know whether we didn'
t have puncture. We had to walk a long way. We had gone further than Brecon. But we came back anyway, and I don't think the bicycle - well we used to think we had a lot of fun with it but I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What happened when you got home, was your mother cross?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, she - wondered where I - where - where we were you know, where this - Gertie Thomas was - and myself. But she wasn't living - she was living - a good way from us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Go? Not when we were children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - my dear no, my mother - when - when the cinema started, you know, putting them up - do you know what she called them? The Devil's work. In Welsh. The Devil's work, that's what she called them, and she was never in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 e a cinema.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about a concert, would you go to a concert while you were still in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, you know especially it if had something to do with school, and I can remember we were doing the Merchant of Venice when we w
ere quite young you know. And Mary and a few of - oh quite a crowd of girls, some from her class and some from mine, and we acted it in our big seat, in Port Morlais. You know, we had an evening to do it. And - I could remember it - as well, and we were q
uite young you know 'cos we were only in the elementary school, but - I think - Mary was the boss, and I think she was Shylock, and - I forget -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In English of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, I think - I forget who Portia was, but we knew our pieces you know. The quality of mercy is not strained, it droppe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  as the gentle rain from heaven. Do you remember it? And we - we did that in chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And you were in the elementary school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you ever go to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not when we were chi
ldren. But - later - oh I'll never forget going to Cardiff, and - Sir Henry Irvine and someone else, I forget - who was there, somebody very notable, my sister now Jane, the wicked one, she was - preparing to get married. And she wanted - buying clothes a
n
d things. And - I had a fur cap on, and it came to rain, and this cap was - dripping down in my face. Well - we went to this - we went to the - this music hall, and we set up in the gods you know. And we could see one of our members there and we said, oh 
w
e're all right, old Sam Davies is over there. So we came now to come - to go home. We'd lost the train. And there wasn't another train. We didn't know what - and we didn't have much money. But I don't know - and we were a bit afraid you know, because - Ca
r
diff at night isn't very safe is it. So we met some gentleman, and we told him our plight, and he said - well we didn't know whether he was good or bad, so he said, I'll take you to my hotel he said. Well - he - he took us to his hotel and he was a perfec
t
 gentleman. And we told him that we didn't have much money. Well we - our return tickets you see were no good to go home. Of course that Jane wouldn't turn a hair but I was frightened to death. And - anyhow we got home, this gentleman said, it'll be all r
ight, and we don't know who he was, but he was a perfect gentleman. We got home, if we did, we had it off my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When did you get home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In the - next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You stayed in the hotel that night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The - the - the first train that we could get to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did your mother say?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
She was furious. Jane of course she was blaming you see 'cos I was younger. And - but we got out of that. But - those are the sort - sort of days we had. I don't suppose many would - although perh
aps some would get much worse then that. But I'll never - 'cos I looked really - like one of them you know, with this cap. And the water dripping down. Of course Jane was a bigger woman, and I was much -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only - when we were children a penny on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have it every Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And you know in those days you'd have a lot of sweets for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only - only our own family. See one helping the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mean your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no. But
 - we did have a relative, Uncle John's daughter from Liverpool - I hope that Dyoreth isn't listening, she was courting a Mr Hughes, and a North Walian. And they couldn't bear him. And - they sent Liza, she was Liza too, she was a lovely girl, sent her to
 
my mother to stay, out of John Hughe's way, 'cos they didn't like him. He came after her.. And he lodged - in a house right opposite us, where they were keeping - lodgers. And - anyhow they got married and they'd a house full of children, and - do you go 
t
o Aberystwyth sometimes? Well now there was a shop there, I don't know whether it was Hughes and John or John and - John and Hughes, a boot shop, beautiful, and they've got - they had them - in different parts. Well that was her - that was Liza's son. She
 
had a house full of children. And one was a minister. And - and then she had another sister, Dorothy, she came down in her widow's weeds. I've never seen such a picture of a girl in all my life. She wore the weeds you know, and she had a - beautiful featu
res, and she was fair and she had a bit of a birth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
maker here, but she was beautiful. And she married - she married - she married a chemist the second time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did this Liza help you at all when she came down to stay with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she was like one o
f us. She was just like one of us, and she lasted like that you see until - until the end. They lived in the Rhondda after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So she used to come and visit you did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, and all my - my mother's - nephews you know, and they were a nice bunch. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any actual relatives living in Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - Liza then, my cousin, and - they got married. And they came to live to Merthyr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well we were all - 
you know, I don't think - I often wonder whether the children today - whether they regard their mother - because - I would break my heart - when my mother was ill. I used to - think what if she - something happened to her you know, and that was always at 
t
he back of my mind. But of course when she died you see she was eighty-six. And she was with my youngest sister - living, 'cos she was a widow, and she said to me - because Catherine had been more spoilt, she said - I want to teach Catherine to live, she 
used to say. But - you'd never - you'd never alter Catherine you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you used to think like that about your mother when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? Always. Did you? When I was a child - but now - do you know, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It used to worry you then did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I tell - I often used to tell these girls - well I don't know, my mother never - had to tell us what to do. But - you see - we used to see it ourselves. She never used to say, the floor wants washing. Or - the dishes are to be washed. And 
we were never allowed to leave a dirty dish - over the night. I expect you do though do you, they do here. They do - they do here. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I wonder why it was like that then, she didn't have to tell you things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never had to tell us. And washing da
y - oh there that was hard work. And there was Mary upstairs, Greta when you coming up, because you see, I was of value up there you know as well. But you know, I wouldn't want to be brought up any other way. That's how I feel. I - I'm so grateful - for t
hings you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Forming character you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents have any friends? You mentioned earlier that your father had a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh and my mother - she had - two - very devout friends, chapel, from chapel, but one was always wantin
g to borrow money. And - her - her daughter - Blod, they did claim some relationship but it's a along way off. Blod married a bank man, and they lived in - Bangor when ET was there. And of course - Blod has taken to like a drop you see. And she's living i
n Merthyr now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents have their own friends, or were the friends your mother's friends or your father's friends or did they have the same friends?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well you see - my mother w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 s - there's old Mrs Jones - Mrs Jones the coal we used to 
call her, they would call in our house - either by going to chapel, or by coming back from chapel, and her husband. Then there was a man by the name of David Williams. He was brought up in the country, and he would call to see us, and he'd bring his troub
l
es to my mother and my mother would tell him, Well David you were no better when you were young you know. Oh they used to come - and a lot - and do you know, people used to come to my mother - and they would have their limbs aching you know. And she used 
- she used to give them a poultice fr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
m cow's manure, and she'd do it for them. And - they used to swear that it was - because - my mother used to say, all the hergs you know, herbs - the - what is it in English, all the herbs and things are in that what th
ey eat, and - oh I - I think she would have made an excellent - doctor. If she'd had the - the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So she had her own friends, your mother had her own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they used to call in like that, and they were friends of my fathers, but you se
e after my father died these two used to come - regularly. And - one was Mrs - Jones, and she was - there was no work in her at all, and - she'd always take her tea on a Friday, and the whole time she'd be playing with her wedding ring all - like that. An
d there was nothing like that about my mother. Oh dear dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would friends visit the house and would they be offered anything to eat and drink? Would they come on any special days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh on a Friday Mrs Jones would always come. But Mrs - the other - the other Mrs Jones - would come when she was hard up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would she be given something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. She wouldn't. But - Mrs - the other Mrs Jones was - she wasn't living very far the other one you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your father's friends, would they come to visit the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Only these men from the country you know would come. And - and these - most of these people in Sunday school were from the - not from the same country as us, but from the country and come to Merthyr - to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they - never were invited.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about neighbours? Would they come in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well they'd come in you know, but you know my mother never encouraged - people - back a
nd fore, 'cos she never went herself. But if they were in trouble - she was always ready. You know, she would always give a - a hand if there was somebody ill or something like that. Oh and they - and they - they were very fond of her you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 People
 often say now that in those days they used to have to make their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they were out with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When they were where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 With their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - my mother never used to go round - houses, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And your father would go out with his pals having a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What classes do you think there were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well we had - we had no - real society you see. Not in Merthyr. There was one family - the Davies's, I don't know whether you've heard of this - rector or curate Dowse, have yo
u? His father used to work for them I know. Well - you'd call - you - you - I don't know whether you'd call them society, but they were a very nice family. And then the others were doctors you see, or - chemists. Of course the chemists were not doing - th
en what they're doing now, I'll tell you sho'se - who'se brother was in the chemist shop in Merthyr, 'cos they are Merthyr people, is that - Johnson's with the - that family you know, 'cos their father went out to Australia you see and made -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What other classes do you think there were in Merhtyr then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well of course there were the - there was some very poor you know. Very poor. And - I can remember now - this is later now when my sister, my eldest sister was married, and Gevartha works you know w
e-e in full swing, and Dowlas works, and - Crowshaw had built - a row of houses - they're - they're standing today and they look really nice, and the people used to - clean those houses on a Friday, and they'd go up on a Saturday to get their pay, to the 
office you see. And the same thing happened in Dowlas. Well we - we gave a lot of debt in Dowlas you know, when the strike was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
on, and - we never - you know, they used to - beg for food and my husband used to say, oh dear, it's very hard on them, and - he was very very kind - the debt that was on our books, if we had it in I would have been very comfortable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was a terrible time then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? Oh terrible. And you see there was nothing like today you know, they couldn't have - well do you k
now, I think there's a lot of it abused. 'Cos I used to often come up from Merthyr in the bus and perhaps a little woman would be sitting next to me and she'd be - boasting - what she could get, curtains - rug for the floor, through this - what do you cal
l it - means test. And - and - and - my doctor used to tell me - how they used to abuse stuff. Used to often tell me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What class or group would you say your family belonged to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I would call them - although we didn't have money, that we were a respectable - class anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - well - our friends were all in - rather nice positions you know - well there's Ellen Anne's father, he was a builder, he owned our house. I would
n't like to tell you what has happened to that lot though. Oh dear dear. And - you know, they were all - respectable, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of people belonged to the other classes? You've mentioned there was one upper class family there you felt?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well the doctors and the - of course they used to go round in their carriages and pairs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of people belonged to the other class the poorer class you were mentioning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well - you know - you know the kind - they couldn't care l
ess. You know, they were - dirty - and - oh - you know, we used to cross this iron bridge to go over to my sister's, and do you know I used to be afraid in the daytime nearly to go for because - they'd - the hovels that they lived in you know. They were v
ery - well no doubt drink was at the end of it see. But of course today you see - people - drink perhaps quite as much, but their positions are better aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mean they can afford it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mean people used to drink then and they couldn't afford it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Mm. But you know - what I feel is - there's nothing to stop people from being clean. Is there? Now - we used to see a lot of filth you know. Mm. Well even - even now our doctor used to tell me that he used to go round these facto
ries now, in Dowlas, and he said, you'd see the girls with curlers, and perhaps in between - there was sores and scabs you know. He said - he's retired now, he's a very nice man, but oh I had a lovely little Polish doctor now, instead of him. And he used 
to tell me a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you ever told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 To show respect in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But Tudor's very keen, though, on - people - not to be afraid to sir, you know. He said, it doesn't take anything out of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there anyone you called sir or madam when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No. Only there was a Newess, she kept a shop and she called it Madam - Madam what was sh
e now, she's dead now - some of the family here too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents, by touching their cap or calling them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not in - not when I was a child, but mind - as we grew - you know if we'd go up - t
own - then - they would touch their hats you know. We had that respect anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who were considered the most important people in Merthyr when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - the Davies's of Bryn Tyrian, they were very nice - country people you know. And
 - mind Doctor Biddle, we didn't think much of him, but there was another doctor that - was my mother's doctor, he was Welsh, and my mother thought the world of him, now there was no nonsense about him at all. He was a clever doctor, but - he wasn't of th
e old school you know like these, it was those who - Doctor Webster and Doctor - Ward, they were all a class you know above - above everybody else you can say. But today it's different you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why didn't you think much of Doctor Biddle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he w
asn't a nice man. He wasn't a nice - natured man you know. But she was very nice. I used to go there for orders for my sister, they used to - buy meat off her you know and she'd give an order, and Mrs Biddle would be in the kitchen you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you come into contact with the Davie's Bryntyrian at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I think they were an older family, and they were considered a very nice family. A very nice family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the shopkeepers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - dear there was - little shops round use you know, they - doing quite well you know selling - they'd make - you'd pass the shop and you could smell - this wonderful cake, four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212583\charrsid7633169  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 pence a pound you know, and made on the premises, Reynolds's, people coming from the country and opening out you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would they mix with, the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Old Seal was a - a - property owner, and he was also an agent you see, and he lived a few doors from us, and - coming down and - saying you know 
that they would - almost kill him. It was terrible. I can remember that. Well they had no money to pay the rent you see, and he was a - he was a very - nasty little man too. And they thought themselves somebody. Mm. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the clergy then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, just respectable you know and the ministers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Usually their church people you know. Their - that's who they would mix with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about teachers, who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, they'd - during my you
nger days, oh poor old Edwards, I'm sure your husband would remember him, he had club feet you know, but he was a wonderful preacher, and a wonderful man. And he had a house full of children, and you see the salary was so very small, I often wonder - how 
they could live. Because - they had very little you know, and - Mrs Edwards was - she was more English than Welsh, but oh he was a lovely man, we could go to him now and he - he would be interested now in our sweethearts and everything. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the teachers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I don't know, the teachers you know, their - they - they didn't seem like they are today. Tere was this - they had to go to a - a sort of - they had a centre, where they used to attend you know. Do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 There were no training colleges then were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And - oh well our friend used to go, but they would go to college later you see. Well it was only a two year course wasn't it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would the teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I don't know, Mary Simm
ons, she was my teacher, and she had long hair and she lived - she lived quite a long way from the school. Well I should think that she'd be glad to get home. But she used to say - very strict mind, she'd say, Marg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ret Davies, you dare glance of this board
, it'll be woe betide you, and her father and my father were big pals. And then she'd come on to me dinner time and she'd say, Greta, she said, will you go down to - Miss Weedon's, that was a little shop for a cake for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 me, a penny cake, for her lunch. Of course they didn't earn the money then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the farmers, were there any farmers in the district?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Lot of farmers up in Cwm Term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well, they would - they'd be a little - set on their own up there. And 
then - my sister married a farmer, well you know, you didn't have a lot of time to bother, if you had - animals to see to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the employers, in the works you see, who would they mix with, were the Crawshaw's living there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They lived
 there for a time you know, the Crawshaw's and of course he had the - he had the - the Castle built you see so that he could see - the works. Of course they say that he was very hard, that's why - I think Socialism you see has come - to - make this differ
e
nce. Oh everywhere. You take it here for instance. Look at all - well of course Lloyd George started this scheme wasn't it, of - mm. Oh my - my - my husband would go as far as Brynmawr to listen to Lloyd George. Mm. Lloyd George's granddaughter has been t
o our house in Merthyr and - they'd have a little prayer meeting, she's a great one with the - Moral Rearmament.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of people would you say went to the church when you were young in Merthryr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - they were very dressed up you know, if t
hat's anything to go by, but Hope chapel too, where - Mrs - who's that, I can never remember their names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - Hope people now I'm telling you, we used to see a lot, they'd be passing our d
oor you see, and they were always beautifully turned out. Well the church people then would be - the doctors more. And - mind Seymour Berry went to the Market Square, Independent. All his family, but they were not considered - nor his wife, his wife's - p
eople - were ironmongers. Mr Sandbrook, a lovely man. One of the nicest men - you'd ever wish to meet. Much nicer character than Seymour's father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - well you know - to the English perhaps they would be - more dressed up, whether they had more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
hristianity I don't know. But they would be far more dressed up than the people that would be going to the Welsh chapels, at that time. But of course - there wasn't much different - now, these days you see
, whether you were church or chapel or doctor or solicitor, 'cos they're all - the same today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living do you think then in Merthyr, or would you say there were different groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well of course you find - you find it today don't you, there are different groups - some - would want to save a bit, others wouldn't have enough to spend. That's the difference you see. It was the - it's - it's the same today you see. Say now you gave - s
omeone a hundred pounds. You gave it to two people, well - one - would hide it perhaps under a bushel, the other would make it go as far as possible, and you get that today don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you think that one group felt superior to the rest then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Da
ys perhaps I didn't have the commonsense to think whether they felt different, but - if there was anything they'd be jealous of one another you see, because - one would buy their own house, perhaps, the other would be paying - and perhaps couldn't pay the
 
rent. And you'd find it if you're in business. You'd find - my husband always used to say - a minister should - spend a year in a business. And then he used to say, when these strikes and things, nothing will bring them to their senses but famine. Always 
said that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were some families thought of as rough than and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. A lot of that. Mm. A lot of it. And they - they would come - they'd come from Ireland you see, most of our customers were - Italians, or Irish, and then the We
lsh people would come - from over the mountain, to get bacon and eggs, bacon and butter chiefly, from our shop. We had a very good business you know. You know - we used to have - calico balls in Merthyr, I don't know whether you've heard of them. They wer
e
 quite - well they were the - you know, quite - as good as any ball but they called them calico balls, and - I was only thinking in bed - the people that went you know - they were - grocers and - drapers, that had done well you know, and doctors of course
,
 and - these regimental people, they all went to the calico ball. Well now there were a few houses - near use you know, opposite, and - their daughter had the Temple of Fashion, and when there was a calico ball - we would all go outside the door, to watch
 her coming out into the cab. A crowd of us you know. And - we used to have great enjoyment to see them dressed up you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why were they called calico balls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well that's what they called it in those days. It was held in the drill hall. And
 of course all the professional people went, and the - the - the trades people that had done well, some had had their - their business left after their parents you know, but - they were in the swing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go, would any of your family go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh
 no. Not to that anyhow. But Jane used to go - of course my mother was against anything like that you see. But Jane would go to a dance. She was the only one that went.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You wouldn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't su
ppose I was interested enough you know. What - what we did you know when we - when we were growing up, we used to take an interest now - in knitting and sewing, doing drawn thread work, and crocheting, all those things. And - you know, we used to enjoy - 
the result of our - of our - hands really, and our brains of course. We used to enjoy that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Craftsmen what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. A - a great difference. Labourers were - 
were really labourers you know. There was a great difference. I can remember that. But mind - I can remember some very nice craftsmen too. Oh he was a very good cabinet maker, I showed you the legs of that chair. And he was lame with one leg you know, but
 he was a wonderful man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In where? Oh I don't think so. Do you know my mother - she was all out for the - lower class. You know. For the respectable lower class. Sh
e would do anything that she could - when she was able to, to help them. And you know now - in Sunday school you'd see - the poorer ones sort of clinging to my mother you know. You know, she had that way about her. Oh no, she never looked down on the bott
o
m dog. Never. And my father - well of course - mind I don't know, I often wonder - where we've had - well you call it pride wouldn't you, where we've had that from, because - you know we've always sort of looked upwards. Some perhaps - I - don't think the
se two girls - I think they're great socialists you know, and - they don't - I was very particular who my friends were you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why was that I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I often think - you know, then Mary my sister older than me, she had far more dignity than I had. I had plenty but she had more than I did.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, but she often used to tell us to lift your heads up as high as anybody in Marthyr. Always told us that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think that, why did she say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well, because you see she - she used to look down more or less on the parish relief you know. And even - even the old age pension - she said to me when I got married - she said, in Welsh it was of course - I've
 saved about three thousand, and she had built two houses you know, so she said - I wont want to bother anybody, I don't want the old age - but you see my brother - started with - this Mervyn Jones's brother - well of course Mervyn couldn't help, neither 
c
ould Ernest Jones, he was a solicitor in Kevan, for they are Merthyr and Kevan people you see, and - John started - feeling money you know, he took over my sister's business and he started speculating and he knew nothing about it you know, 'cos he was a d
eacon in chapel. But you know my mother gave him every penny she possessed. The place in the country, and - us girls the - the bit of money we had, poor old Mary, she had a few golden sovereigns, gave it to John. And there -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 This was before the first world war, was this during the first world war or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - oh after the first world war it would be. But you know there's mistakes people make don't they, and John now went up to London, and he had been very kind to Francis Noyle, I don't know wh
ether - Doctor Francis Noyle, an Minister with us, from - Llangeneth - - and he came to Merthryr in an office, and he decided that he would go up to Kevan to - Batherine Davies who was a very scholarly man, and he went up to have lessons, and do you know 
t
hat John, he was in the station then, he housed him during the time that he was having these lessons, 'cos he couldn't afford - to pay for lodgings or anything like that. Well - John went up to London you know afterwards, and - poor old John, he was - Mr 
N
oyle - was wonderful to him. Wonderful, he was now Doctor Francis Noyle, and - he had got on well you know, but - John could always go there when he wanted to. But - he - he had the children, and his wife you know, although she was from quite a scholarly 
family, but she - she wasn't much of a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you think it was possible in the time when you were young for people to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know, we never touched the - upper class, and today when I think of it you see - they
 were really no better. You know, like you think today of the boys that are doctors and solicitors, they've come on haven't they through - but you see, in those days - they thought themselves somebody you know. Oh I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You can't remember anybody going sort of from the working class into the upper class or the middle class in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Occasionally you would. We had - Mr Edwards, he was the - Mis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  Majesty's Inspector you know, one of the highest, he married a German lady, a very nice family, and 
I remember - a very ordinary little fellow - got quite friendly with them you know. I don't know whether you've heard - of Toska Davies, he married - a teacher here, well -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I can remember my mother telling me - Mr Sandbrook, he was a - an Independent, and he kept an ironmonger's shop - and it was his daughter that married Seymour Berry. Lord Buckland. Now I remember my mother - oh it's a long story. Tere was a man by the
 name of Dan Davies who used to call him, Dan Davies the pigs, he was a - a - you know, dealing in cattle and - sheep and all the rest of it, and he was quite well off, short little man, he was the conductor or - the - a huge - choir in Merthyr before the
s
e here - before Harry Evan's time you know, and - I remember my mother saying - my sister - they had a butchers shop in Newport you know and they were doing quite well, but Fred had a brain - something the matter with his brain, a disease, and - somebody 
t
old my mother to have - her daughter from - Newport - to Merthyr for her to be near us. Well now, Fred stayed down with his mother because he was so ill, and he was an excellent fellow you know. And she never went into the business when he was alive, beca
u
se he - did it all and he went out to Chepstow - to buy - to buy stuff for the shop - you know. Well - my mother was very uneasy, and there was a butchers shop there and it was owned by Dan Davies, and - so Jane took the shop, and she took a lease on it y
o
u know. And the lease had gone out now. So she said - he said to Jane - now he said, you shall have a fresh lease, he said, if you promise that you will buy all - with me, 'cos she was doing - quite a nice trade. My other sister was able to help her you s
e
e. And - help her about the joints and different things. And - so she thought it over, 'cos it was a nice looking shop. And there was a - so she told my mother, and my mother said, you'll do nothing of the kind, she said. She said, you're not signing anyt
h
ing. She said, there's that shop opposite, the Wilkins kept it, it was a - a paper shop you know, and - it wanted doing up you know. Oh - mammy she said, you are not going to that old shop she said, about this shop. So my mother - it was - owned by Mr - S
a
ndbrook, and my mother went down to see Mr Sandbrook, and - he said - he didn't ask for a - a - what you - what's - what do you call the money you put down. Mm? He didn't ask for a deposit. He shook hands with her, and he said in Welsh, the shop is yours.
 
And that was all. And my mother said she had never dealt with such a gentleman. But as for Dan Davies - and do you know it's very pathetic, of course he lived in a - he was a showman you know, and he lived - he had a beautiful house at the bottom of the A
venue, just by the general hospital. It's there now. Do you know that his son is gone away - with a barmaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember anyone being described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I could describe many. Well I can tell you this now, that I used to consider
 Mrs Jones, my Sunday school teacher, one of the - oh she was a darling. I was very fond of her. Her daughter, the one that I said she was in college you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You did mention last week that Mrs Sandbrook you thought?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mrs Sandbrook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That Mrs Sandbrook was a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mr Sandbrook was a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, she was a very - retiring little woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or was it the daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well the daughter - like you know - she was a pretty girl, and Seymour fel
l for her, but she was one of these quiet little things you see, because - Ironmongers they were and they were not - he didn't try to be in the swim with anybody you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there anyone else then in Merthyr you thought of as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Let me think now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we - we - we were more frightened than anything of his uniform I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know, I suppose it was because - you know - the law I expect it was that we were a bit - afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course - I think - they were more respected then than they are today. I think. Of co
urse he - my dear to put up with a tremendous lot of fights in Merthyr. Oh it was terrible. Frightening really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why was that I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I think they would be drinking and they'd argue you know, and they'd have a real good old fight you know. W
ell - talk about that Ali. That man that had his jaw.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was it because it was a mixed community, you mentioned there were a lot of Irish and Italians there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm. Tremendous lot. Especially - in Dowlas. They'd come over to the works you see. And mi
nd some were very nice. Very nice they were. And the Irish you know, of course our books were nothing but debt you know because - they would have the food you see, but they didn't trouble - how they paid for it, and - I don't know whether this would inter
e
st you. We had a young lady in the shop, she was a Catholic, and she'd been with us for about fourteen years, with my husband, before I got married. And - some of the customers you know she did the books you see and some of the customers they'd say - well
 
are you going to pay anything off now Mrs - so and so, off your debt? No, they were not willing - they were not willing to - to pay off, but what she would do, when she'd be counting up their account, perhaps she'd put a shilling or two on you see, to the
 
account, and they were paying that off the ac - the debt, so - she was such a Catholic that she asked - the - Father you know, if she was doing the right thing? And he said, yes, she was doing - the - the - what you ought to do, he said, to make them - re
alize what honesty meant, and of course - it would be taken off their account you know. And they were not scholars enough you see to - to know that but she - did it - very honestly. So she was very - she was an awfully nice girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mentioned earlier that your home was rented in Castle Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well we were so friendly - with his daughter you know. Well they - she was one of our - friends. And of course he had the big window made into a smaller window.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well he never bothered us somehow. And I'm wondering - I think the rent must have been - very reasonable I should imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you say there was a lot of fighting going on, you were living right in the centre weren't you of Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So perhaps you were seeing it all weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course it was much worse you see - they would have - fights like that on the high street. 'Cos there were no motor cars
 hardly - hardly ever see a motor car. A cab - and of course we used to see - the doctors and the solicitors coming downin their carriage and pair you know, to the office in the morning. And - they'd be down shopping you see. 'Cos they'd keep a coachman o
f
 course. Of course - and when you think of it, when I think of it today you know - they were really no better than any of us were they. Only that they happened to get on, and of course you see we didn't have - we didn't have - doctors free in those days. 
We had to pay. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh I think so. I think my mother did. I don't think my mother could care less. But - I can remember as we were growing up you know, she was very ill 
one day, and - she said, I'd like to see John, my only brother you see. So we sent for John, to London, and - she had the doctor, Doctor Cromwell Jones, a very nice man, now he didn't pretend to be anybody but he was a very clever man. And - so she said -
 
well, I don't know how I am going to pay the doctor, she said to me, well mammy dear I said we will pay the doctor. And do you know what she said to me? If you have anything give it to John. See? She worshipped him. But she - she - she managed to buy a su
it of clothes for him anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you feel then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh terrible. Mm. Do you know there was a - a talk - Sunday night, you were in chapel I expect. And - there was a lovely old man, I think he had been - sort of governor - in the prison. But not - with the same affection as I loved my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your father died when you were young you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had much more to do with your mother didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. And - when he was alive you see. And we were always ready to help her you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you think about it now when you felt that she had a struggle? How did you feel about it when you felt she was struggling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course - we couldn't help very well you know. And she said to me - Gretta, she said - there was a M
rs Denn, and she had a house full of children, and she wasn't very - well, she - I don't think she had the energy, you know, to do anything so my mother said to me, go down, she said, and see if you can do something for her or a Saturday. Well - she put m
e
 to wash the lavatory, and - she didn't have a clean spot in the house, I said to my mother, I'm not going down, she give me a penny see. I'm not going down to that house again I said. Filthy. So my mother said - didn't bother you know. But she was always
 
ready to help. She used to - she used to find people now when she'd take them milk you know round. She used to see them struggling you know. And - I don't know whether you remember - a very young Labour MP, and he married a little girl from Merthyr, Thoma
s
. What was his name now, he died pretty young. But he was very popular. And - his - mother-in-law, Mary Morgan, she was a daughter to that - Morgan's the butcher that told my father about the big seat you know. But Mary was a very nice girls, she was the 
e
ldest daughter. And she was teaching you know, I don't know whether she went to college, but she was a teacher, and - she had two daughters, and a delicate husband, this Thomas was, and this little MP married one of the daughters, Gladys and - my mother w
a
s saying - when she was taking the milk to Mary, to - to - Mrs Thomas - she used to put down every item - that she used to spend you know. You know, because she didn't have - much to spare you see, and she was bringing the two girls up. You don't know any
thing about that side of life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Things had improved by the time we were being brought up hadn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, yes. Mm. Yes, see I'm going back years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You are going back to the period before the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Mm. And do you know
 - I - I feel ashamed when I think of it. We were going to school you know, clean. And my poor mother, she didn't have an overall to put on. And do you know what she used - and - and my friend you know, old Williams the builder's daughter - she always had
 
beautiful pinafores. Beautifully laundered and all the rest of it. And my mother would put a big handkerchief - she'd pin one corner up here, and the others round here. I feel when I - I used to be ashamed you know. But you see - what could we do? And I c
ould have been dressed - equally as good as anybody. If my father had - but there you are. But my - now my youngest sister, she - fared better than I did see, because the older girls now could buy an overall and give it to her but I didn't have one.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But you didn't realize when you were a little girl that it was your father, because of that that you couldn't have these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I - no. You know - you know - a - a child really is indifferent until they get - a bit older, you see. Yes. No. But you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But you did notice a difference between your pinny and the other girl's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. But you know - old Katie, she would cling to me, but you know now - I don't want this to go down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What difference did it make to the family when your father was
 ill or out of work? This was the position with you all the time really, your father wasn't working was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So your mother had to do it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did she ever have to get help from the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. She didn't try for it, whether she needed it I don't know. But - oh she worked hard. And she was so clean with it all you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When there was someone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Merthyr. T
hose riots you know. And - she lived - a few doors higher than us, of course - he didn't used to take any notice of us, he was a - a - a - house agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That was the case, they disapproved of him didn't they, that Seal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The people didn't like him did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they couldn't bear him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did they actually do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh, they - well he dare not show his face, and you see - he was fortunate that he could go - out to the back, and the same back they had as we had you see, you know,
 a row of houses. Mm. And - he - he was a bit of a pig of a man I think you know, he didn't - I used to tell David off. I used to tell my husband often you know - if you came out of the - if you came out with the council I used to tell him, you'd get in e
a
sily because - he was such a nice man you know. He was so kind to everybody. The three of us - do you know three of us married Davies's. And we were Davies before. So I do call mine David, and - 'cos - my younger sister married a David Davies. And we both
 lived in Dowlas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you ever given any lessons by your parents, you went to school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do you remember how old you were when you went to school first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I - I - well - I suppose I'd - I'd go you know - the ear
liest possible age, but - I - all I can remember in school, we had a - a needlework mistress - she was - quite English, and she had her teeth - very much projecting you know, but she was - she was a nice old soul, I can remember her now teaching us - plai
n sewing you know. And different things like that. But you see - today - perhaps you were the same - not one of these girls use a thimble. Do you? I can't sew without a thimble can you
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What time you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - we used to go at nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What time would you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh about half past four I think. But - we had a headmistress. Oh - talk about a serpent, and she was always beautifully turned out, and she - she was so strict she looked the headmistress. Oh dear dear. Old M
iss Jenkins. Well if you remem - if you're an Independent you were all right. But the Independent and Methodists were right opposite you see. And - she used to favour them you know which was wrong. And - she - when we'd have an exam you know and we - when
 
we were - kiddies, she'd tell us to put on our - best things, and see that your shoes were nice and clean, and - oh and we were there - 'cos the inspectors used to come round. And the floor would all be sawdust. I can remember that quite well. And there w
as old Miss Jenkins, she be like a duchess you know, and she - she walked like a headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was it a mixed school, were there boys there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No - there was a boys school, and her brother was the headmaster of the boys school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was a girls school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, to a girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was the board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - we used to go - there was a - a long tip to go up, quite near our house again, you know, we were in the ce
ntre of everything. There was - that tip to go up, and I can see the little Prince of Wales - going up the other tip when he came to visit - before he - before he ab - abducted you know. Up the other tip now, that tip took you to Brecon Road. And our tip 
was Aber Morlais tip. They're there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long would it take you to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd there in five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who went with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Always Katie Will}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ams, this girl with the nice - and she was a pretty girl. She was very pretty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh at home. No - there was - no - school dinners in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I quite enjoyed it you know. Mind - I don't want to boast, I think I was quite a - an average scholar you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I liked it. But Jane couldn't bear it. The wicked one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - oh I got on all right with them. Mary Simons who - she used to say Marg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 a
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ret Davies, you dare glance of this board. Oh dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I don't think so. Mind Miss Jenkins was inclined that way, the headmistress. Yes. But I think - mind she pretended to be a great Christian but I think she was a hypocrite myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they'd be sent out you see. I was never sent out for a cane thank goodness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would they have to do to be caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course - one big thing would be - cheating. You know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, isn't it strange, you know, Nina often says now - that it's the home influen
ce. Well you see my mother couldn't speak English. She didn't know much English.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your schooling was in English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But I don't know, somehow or other - we seemed to get on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you know any English before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 W
ell I must have known because - you see - now today - they're inclined to talk a lot of Welsh aren't they. Now - as soon as we go out from the - from our steps - it was English, with all the children round. You see? So I lost that beautiful Welsh. And we 
didn't practice it you see. Only with my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother ask you about what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I don't think she did. We'd tell her you know things, and she - she'd be quite interested you know. We never - we never missed school you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would she meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the other children in the school come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Some better, some worse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mentioned just now the headmistress about the Independents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, that headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But not the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not the teachers, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I think there must have been. Because - you know some would mix you see and they wouldn't be - coming to school like - other children, and of course we had - what we used to call the whiper in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The Attendance Officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was he much in evidence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, yes, and it all depended - now I was telling you about that council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 or, that was a Labour - now - he was an Attendance Officer, later on in life, and a very nice man. In fact his son now is a headmaster of one of those schools near Aberfan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I didn't try my scholarship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I was young. Mind I was very silly not to have gone - not have tried the scholarship see, my mother couldn't afford to pay }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
pence a week. And if I'd passed the scholarship like Mary did I wouldn't have had to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How old were you when you left school, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Couldn't have been more than twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I - it was never a bore to me you know. You know, I was very fond of - I was very fond of arithmetic. Very fond of reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you attend any part time education afterwards, any evening classed or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Not until - oh years afterwards. We would go - we had - the evening classes were coming now you see when we were growing up
. And - I told you about Mary going to Cardiff did I. And - of course she had her diploma. Oh no, well now Mary - she couldn't - I told you that she had this cold - that she had this chill in her blood, and very disappointed because - she was very able. A
n
d so there was nothing for her to do now but to - start sewing, she never went to have her trade you know. I can never remember Mary having a trade. But - she worked and worked - she well in fact - she used to go out and - people now - you're asking me no
w
 - about - I can remember the people of Ygoitre, they were - sort of semi-retired. Very nice people they were Ad Mrs Jones - would send - their man that they had on the - on this little farm - to fetch Mary's machine, and she would go - there and sew you 
k
now, for her. Well you know, it wasn't a big - I don't know whether it was a shilling a day or - but - they were always ready to have her. Well she couldn't have been very dull or they wouldn't want her would they. Well she went on like that you know. Unt
i
l - she worked up a business. She didn't go out. She didn't go out at all after - a certain age. And - but she had plenty of places - where they'd like to have her, have they got that there now? Yes. Yes. And a fortnight - and Mrs Jones used to say - and 
s
he was quite a lady, a bit snobbish mind - they were an old Methodist family you know, but the girls had turned English, and - the old mother was lovely, old Mrs Jones, she was a perfect old toff in her manner. And - but anyhow, Mary worked herself up so 
t
hat she had - quite a big business you know at the end, and she - she - she didn't think that - dressmaking was very - you know, that there was much - it didn't have - it didn't have the - the status that a teacher would have. So she decided then that she
 
would go to Cardiff to take - to take these lessons. Do you know that she would go in the morning, and she wasn't strong. She'd catch the train to Cardiff, well you see, I think it was half a crown it was return then. From Merthyr to Cardiff. And she'd ca
tch the train to Cardiff. She'd have the lessons in the - in the college, and it was girls - like Gethlin Lewis's daughter, and those - very high ups in Cardiff that were going there for their own use.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She'd do - work hard there. They'd - M. H. Edwar
ds you know, Falmouth Road, he was a minister there, and Mrs Edwards, she was one of the Samuels, they're related to - a sister-in-law to - what's that - what - what's her name now, she's a - a - member of Parliament, and she's had - she's Lady - Sommersk
i
ll. Isn't it, Summerskill. Well now that was Mrs Edwards's sister-in-law, she married a Samuel you see. Yes. Well now - that family - they were - and they - the - the children they, they were about the same age, there was Tudor, Nina, and - Mrs Edwards's 
- two boys, he is now - the - Town Clerk of Colwyn Bay - the youngest boy. And - they'd go - on horseback you know, to Sodan Monaiave, and they'd have a marve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 lous time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you meet the same people year after year there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well nearly always. So
metimes - we'd meet different ones, Jack Hope would be there, the minister you know, and - old - David used to love it because - you know there was - he had a lot in common with 'em somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you do there? What sort of things would you do on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh well we - we were such a crowd n the house, and they had the seat in frong you know, and we used to make - such a lot of - our enjoyment now - James my brother-in-law, he met - you know, Miss Richards his wife - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 his wife, she's a sister to J.Q.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
 Riachards the solicitor here, he was the first Lord Mayor of Cardiff, and he married her and she was - well he was retired, and she was an old maid you can say. Oh, my godfather. She - well he - he met her there when he was on holidays, but he told
 me when she was - very ill once, well he said - I don't know whether I'm paid back, 'cos I think - he was very fond the ladies in his day you know and I think because - because he was a fine built man - but - oh she was - you know, he liked a bit of good
 
food you see, and she would buy the cheapest old stuff, remember her cooking once - and you could smell the meat. It wasn't fresh. And when she died he wouldn't go to anyone, only to me. And he said - well look Jim, I says, your nieces are in nice positio
ns and they are much younger than I am. Oh he wouldn't hear of that. He wouldn't hear of it, and - he was a big man, I - I used to make his shirts, make his pyjamas. And - he'd be in an old - S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 rgeant in the police force and he was very suspicious. Well I u
sed to go and buy the material, make these shirts, and you can just imagine, Welsh flannel they were, the shirts. And his pyjamas. He'd give me money to - but I used to - take the bill back to him you know. And when he broke; his home when he said - asked
 if he could come to us, do you know I nearly broke my heart. He was very difficult. Well I had dermatitis you know through nerves I think it was. And - and he - and then he'd had this operation - for bladder trouble, and he got a bit mental you see.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you had the children young, how would you spend Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - very - very often I'd take them down to see my mother you know to Marthyr. Yes. 'Cos we could go on the - on the - tram car then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, Sunday
. Well - David would go to chapel in the morning, he'd go to Lybanus, Dowlas, 'cos was too far to go to Merthyr, and - then we'd all go down - I think the children would go to - Herman Sunday school, then we'd all go down in the evening. 'Cos - you know, 
to - only - latterly that we used the car to go to chapel. Used to use that then when the children were older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you or the children put on different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, always. We had our Sunday clothes. Today's so different isn't it. Hats. Hats and all, everything different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well do you know I never used to knit or sew on Sunday. Even - even up - when I was married. But I'll knit here see now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you think it wrong then, why was that, why wouldn't you do it then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know, perhaps it's because I'm not able to go to chapel you see, I'm not able to enjoy - a sermon because I can't hear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were busy in those days, you wouldn't have time to sit and knit or sew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I never wanted to somehow. 'Cos we shouldn't do it at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But did you think it wrong yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - it's a funny thing, when I'm doing it no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 
w, I - I think seven days thou }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 halt labour and do all they work, you know, there's something telling me. And I'm reading now a book about Mother Teresa. Have you read it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you allow the children to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. They never - they - they never wanted to somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You attended a place of worship, Calv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 nistic Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How often would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I'd try and go - to prayer meeting on a Monday night, and on a Thursday you see. Those were our meetings, but I didn't used to go down - after I got married to Sunday school. Because it was too much of an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ffo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 t you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go in the Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would you go on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he would go to Lybanus you see in the morning. Welsh - our - either the Lybanus or Herman. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How often would he got?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he was pretty regular. And of course before he was married you see - he would be down Sunday school because he had a Sunday school class.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He didn't go after he was married to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I don't think so, not when the children were small anyhow. He'd go to - he'd go to Herman, he was quite a - as much at home in Herman, and in Lybanus, because - like he had lodged up there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you belong to a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 E.T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
's you know, he was our choir master, and - you know, he was very good too. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the chapel run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well when I was much younger the - we had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I'm thinking about when you were married and you had the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no. No. But - years ago they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They didn't have anything when you had Tudor and Nina?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any clubs with the chapel then after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only a - a - we'd have a competitive concert you know - very nice, and - we'd make up little concerts ourselves, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Mr Davies go to the weeknight services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Whenever he could. But - very often he was - wasn't able to go you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Because of the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Sunday school, would the children go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
They would go to - now we moved from Dowlas, we moved to Pendaren you see, they were getting older, and - the house that we lived in - Dowlas - it - we had an awful storm there you know, a
nd it was very high up. So - this house was for sale, and - it was between Merthyr and Dowlas. So of course the children then could go to Ratcliffe Hall and - Nina was a - a little Sunday school teacher there, in Ratcliffe Hall, and Tudor would go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What denomination was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The same as - Forward Movement you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The Presbyterian church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Calv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
nistic Methodist became Presbyterian didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would it be English or Welsh there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 English chiefly, yes.
 And I'll tell you who Nina used to call - to take him to Sunday school - but he didn't go to - you know this Aubrey Jones, he's a - his father. His father. His father was blind, and Nina would call there, and take him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 There's some very famous people come out of Merthyr aren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh very. Especially Gefarther School, Gefarther and the Country, they've turned out some wonderful - boys and girls you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did Tudor and Nina go to any of the adult or family services at the chapel? Was it only Sunday school they went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well, I - I can't remember - I can't remember them - you see - it - we were so far from the chapel, that I can't re - you know, when they start school - they got home work to do, and of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 
course, I'm afraid that our - se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 t and things, they were never hardly there. But it was mostly for - eld - old - older people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were the children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I did usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Mr Davies at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He'd teach them in Welsh. You know, he'd teach them the Our Father which art in Heaven. Oh yes, they always said their prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 After you were married did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I think I take more interest now when I'm nearing the grave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What were your views then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, chiefly I think - I think my father and mother were Liberal you see, and - we were all out for Pritchard Morgan and D.A. Thomas.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about after you married, did your views change at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know what you are but I - I never voted Labour. Although mind we've got a lot to thank them for. I'm -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I think he'd go Liberal or Tory, I - I - you know - you look at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well, you look, now at the Merthyr Express the week. There's a row of them there, one applied, all the others nearly are Labour. I - and you know - they - I don't know, they don't seem to be intelligent enough somehow. That's how I feel about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about in the first world war after you were married, do you remember voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Yes. Well - let me see now. Yes, I always went to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your husband go to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you remember what you voted for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well it - it would be either Liberal it would be. More so - now, now I like Heath because - he's given me a little pension you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you or your husband ever feel under pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, but I remember - I remember - one of our neighbours, Davies the Mount, he was coming out, I don't know what his - I think he must have been Independent, and I remember my husband speaking on his behalf you know, bec
ause - he keen - he was a publican, but a very nice old -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 This was in a local election was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Mm. And he got in too, but I was telling David, look if you came out yourself you'd be in on top because I said you've given such a lot of credit - an
d they used to say, oh Mr Davies the Borough Stores, he's such a nice man, they used to say you know. I think he would get in flying boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You don't remember him working for any of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. He would work more now - for anyt
hing to do with chapel. See? If there was - a big meeting, and if Doctor Matthew's there he always stayed with us you see. He - the shop would be second with him then you see, he'd be down because - he was the treasurer - and he'd see that he'd have - a c
o
uple of good bags from the Midland Bank to put the collection, and of course we used to have wonderful coll - and I used to tease him, go on, I said, it isn't - Doctor Martin or his sermons, it's the collection you are thinking of, I used to tease him you
 know, but oh he was very - very fond - he was very fond of the ministers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were you ever a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Only - I told you that we went to - Seymour Berry's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 After you married, would your husband be a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - you know, when you're in business, you can't show - you - you dare not show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He wouldn't take part in any political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you were not doing hour work how did you spend your time? After you were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Always sewing. Always making for them. 'Cos you see, I never spent a penny - on - dressmaking for the children. I would make them and - I wasn't ashamed for anybody to see them. Their coats and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had a lot of work to do then didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Their coats and all. I remember going to Cardiff when we - Nina was in college now. She had started in college, and we went to Hall's, and there was a very smart rig out there, and of course you had to have coupons, and in those days twelve guineas 
was quite a bit wasn't it to pay, today you'd have to pay forty perhaps. So - I looked at this, and I said, look, Nina, I said, I can make you. And I had - I - it's a funny thing you know years ago - they would have sales in Llanuted, my brother-in-law wa
s
 the architect of the factory, and they would have sales for peo - visitors. And we'd buy perhaps twenty pounds worth of - material you know, beautiful tweeds. And - so I said, I'll make one for you. Do you know, you couldn't tell the difference. I copied
 
it - I - the skirt was a - in - what do you call this - furry material? Angora. The skirt was Angora, in the same shade as the green that was in the check of the coat. It was very smart. Well do you know she went to college - and she looked - and she had 
- a little tailored hat to go with it. And Auntie May, she was a big critic, my sister, and she said well Getta, she said, you have made it beautifully for her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You would spend most of your time sewing really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Mr Davies, how would he spend his time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well now she went - we went to - she went to college, one of the girls had bought that very costume. Oh David would - if he - on Thursday afternoon now he'd go - and cut the lawn, and while he was there the people t
hat were passing, and they'd start talking to him, the lawn wouldn't be half cut. You know, he - he couldn't - that was his nature. See, he wasn't a - a wealthy man when he died you know. He wasn't - well - and I wasn't having - I wasn't even having a - w
idow's pension, but I've - jogged along. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would he do other than that in his spare time, how would he spend an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he'd read. You know, he'd read the Goleiad and - all the Welsh papers that came out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well we couldn't very well you see because the children. We couldn't go - very well because - you know, there were no baby sitters in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When did Mr Davies get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, it varied.
 He'd have a cup of tea in the - in the shop perhaps, well if he were - didn't have a meeting he'd come home but I - he'd have a cooked meal you see. And of course - Nina wasn't such a - she wasn't such a glutton as Tudor, but Tudor would have a share of 
you know, whatever was going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - some evenings he would be off - always Friday he'd be come, but it would be late, and Saturday. But the other - you know there was so many different - callings. For - and he took and interest in it. But I was never afraid - how he'd come home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many evenings would you spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well if I wanted to go - if I wanted to go to Cardiff now I'd go with one of my sisters, and David would come home Th
ursday afternoon you see. 'Cos the little maids that we had you know were not very reliable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did either of you go to any clubs, institutes or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I was very keen on - I never coll
ected mind, but I was very keen on - what do you call these certificates, I was very keen on those, and - I am still keen I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You wouldn't have any sort of funeral club or anything like that, or sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did either of you take part in any sport? Like bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or cricket, football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well you see David was - David's very tall you know, and - he wasn't stout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 
 like your husband. Now Uncle J}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ames was like - you're your husband. Well built you know. But David wasn't well built. 'Cos - Lisa was asking me last week - when did y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 ou start getting fat mam}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 . So I had to show her my photo where I was very slim, and - because she said - mammy isn't stout she said. Mm. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She's like her father probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. But - I think she's looking pretty good now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did either of you bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Well - I think - we had a flutter once - on - the Derby, oh only a shilling or something, no. I don't believe in gambling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
If there was something good we'd manage - somehow, we'd have somebody - Mary or somebody would come and look after the children, if there was something good on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No - concerts - concerts as a rule, but Bryn my - my ni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 ece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 's husband was the conductor, and he used to have very good - he'd have David L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
oyd and - Isabel Bailey you know. We would go to that, was a joy. Do you know - if I only hear that David L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 oyd, the tears come to
 my eyes. Do you like him? Oh I do too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I try everything. I - yes I did, I went to - painting class. That was one hobby. I'd have a pop at anything, you know. Wood carving. And - well I try everything, and - if there was any cookery, I'd have a gadget for every blooming thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You like cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I liked it then. But do you know now yesterday - I said to Nina, look, if you want -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any interests outside the house, the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, not much. On
ly - whatever interest there was in the chapel, I would be one of the first there. But apart - I didn't take any - I wasn't in for the hospital, but I didn't seem to have time somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go out to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Only to - you know - a p
icnic or an outing, mind - I had - a very nice time in Chester - a friend of ours, she was the - bank manager's dau - wife, and she - took - I wasn't named you see, she took my sister Jane, Catherine and Mary, she only had a gig, and Jane said to me, oh G
etta, she said, I wish you were with us. So they pushed me in, we had a wonderful time. She took us to Liverpool, and we used to pretend we were a Sunday school class you know going over, oh we had a marvellous time. Oh we had some nice outings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did anyone outside the home help you to look after the family? You emotioned the little girls you had, but would you any relations or friends?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only my sister Mary, when - the children were born, and if I wanted to go - now - to a conference, you know 
- she would look after the children. I felt you know I was happy. But of course one time I couldn't go because - Nina had diphtheria. And we went to Boulogns that year. And we had a wonder - well you ought to see the spread you know. And old Thomas Panywe
r
n, he was a great teetotaller and he was sitting opposite me, in - in this - and I was ashamed to drink you know anything. 'Cos I - I didn't mind taking wine or anything, but he - his fact was a like a figure - you must know him, know them, 'Cos she was a
 big woman with the sisterhood and all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had relatives living nearby, but they were not very near you were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They were some miles away really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In Barry you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They were some miles away, your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How far away would they be, your mother was in Marthyr wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well the others would be in - near Aberystwyth you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had no one really near you did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Only that - this Uncle from Liverpool, his daughter m
oved. You see. I - I tell you, yes, well - he stayed with us you know, we nearly kept him, well - my Uncle never liked him you see, and - at the end although she had a - houseful of children, I don't know that he didn't have an affair with some woman, but
 - that's nothing to do with this is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any friends you know as well at that time after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you see them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh in chapel usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you share the same friends with your husband or would you have your own separate friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, he knew them all you see. You know - he was one of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your husband have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, he was very popular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh very often. Now I'
ll tell you one that used to come a lot and I've never been to see him - J.R. - John we used to call him, J.R. Morgan, he was a member, I don't know whether he wasn't a deacon, in - Pembroke Terrace, because he's getting on now, and - he was in my wedding
, and I've never been to see him. He married - he married the second time. I'd love to see old John.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I - as a rule they'd have a supper, good old meal you know. Because you know - the shop you see, I had the shop at the back of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you say the friends invited in were your friends or your husband's friends, or friends that you shared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well friends we shared usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - my only neighbours you see there were two houses, and they were related - they were Jews, the Friedmans, very wealthy, well it was - it was - the lady nurse that - the nephew had - she told me about the incontinent you know, she came to live -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well not often, we never used to go out much - you know, to have a meal. Now I'll tell you another thing - J.R. Thomas, he was a deacon, and he'd co
me up to our house - about twice a year to do the books you know. David would be the treasurer, and he would be the - and his wife now is in - a home in - in - Swansea, and we had her down here for a day. Yes. And she's got her only son, helps a - he's a 
doctor, and this - I don't think - that she's very fond of her daughter-in-law, I think she's English.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
When you went with your friends or neighbours what would you do, people often say that you had to make your own amusements in those days, what would you do when you got together with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, I don't know, we never seemed to be - at a loss for anything you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 There was no television or anything then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But - we always managed - now on a Friday night they'd come to our house, this was before I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh after we were married they'd come up to see us you know, but - I don't think that we were very great visitors ourselves. But we were always pleased to see - they were nearly all chapel people you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In Dowlas it was. But we bought Penybryn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you rented the home did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they used to come in - and poor old grandpa Friedman we use to call hi
m, he would tell us of - all about when he came - to Merthyr, when he came to Merthyr a poor man with a pack on his back and - you - he died worth thousands. But his wife, she'd go - round Dowlas to look at the cheapest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So your neighbours really o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ned it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 YES. Oh great neighbours-, and we were there when - two of them died you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh very nice. Well you see, they were furnishers as well, so we bought all our furniture, and carpets there, when we got married you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
And of course you didn't move from the community that you'd lived in before, it was the same community that you'd lived in before you were married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You see - only that - Dowlas to me is a strange - because I never made
 Dowlas my home. See, my chapel was in Merthyr, my home was in Merhtyr, my friends - nearly all in Mer - although mind, you know Mrs Evans, she's from Dowlas, I'd like to meet her. I must -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The same district really you were living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. But of course David was more at home - we - he was equally at home in Dowlas, as he was in Merthyr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, I did. I told you didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your parents help you in setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh yes, my mother. She - she gave me all the pillow cases and the feather bed. And the tubs. And even a mangle you know, those old - everything. Everything that you could - she did it all, and she gave - e
ach of us - twenty pounds - different times you know, and I was silly enough see, Tom Rhys was interested in Pandarne cinema, I put mine in there and it all went. And my mother said work of the Devil she used to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 W
ell, well - he was on the excise in - in - Mumbles, in Swansea, what do you call it you know when you come - not at the excise, what do you call these - he was a - a witness, what do you call it? On the Jury, he was on the jury in Swansea, and Mary and I 
were spending a holiday - in - Mumbles, and he used to come down in the evening to the Mumbles, and that's when it really started, you know, he was tel - talking more to Mary than to me. That's when it really started, as - anything serious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long was that then before you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I should think it would be about - three years. Because I remember going - spending a lovely holiday with him - in - in Mumbles in a beautiful hotel there, and - of course I was a bit shy you know, and - there were som
e Merthyr people staying there, and - but he was such a gentleman. There was nothing common about him you know. Nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Do you know who - do you know who - one was in my wedding? I don't know whether you kn
ow J.R. Morfan, he was a bank manager, and he was going to Pembroke Terrace. And he lives - it's in the directory, I'm supposed to go and see him, he had a brother - he was from near Bronant you see, so he used to spend a lot of his time with us, in Merth
y
r, when he was in the bank in Merthyr, and - he used to say oh I'm bound to come to your wedding Getta, and - the place was - well there were no end there and I was going quite early about eight in the morning, because we were going straightaway to - Lond
on for our honeymoon. And - there was a - a car to take us down, not to have any fuss you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was it like, how many guests did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I didn't have a wedding breakfast you see. No. WE went straight away from chapel. But - but there
 were - there were - plenty, and men especially, in the wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Had gone to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, friends of ours you know, all friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What actually happened, can you remember it, who went with you, who gave you away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who gave me away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 MM? Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She didn't go to the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. She was oldish you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It must have been my brother that gave me away. My brother. John, yes, he gave me away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have bridesmaids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was quiet really but there were a lot of people in the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Very - very quiet yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't really have any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But we had a tremendous lot of presents. Oh - well, I've got some of them ther
e now. And some that Nina's given away I think. Trouble is I knew so - he was so - popular you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He already had a business sin Merthyr then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In Dowlas. And - then - used to come - walk down - my sister Catherine, younger than me, she married
 in Dowlas, quite - a nice - a nice - home they had you know and he had a very nice job under Guest Keene, this was Glyn's father, very intelligent. Very intelligent boy, and he had a wonderful position, and we used to spend a lot of our time - there, wit
h
 Catherine, and - perhaps it would be - getting on for twelve when he'd walk down with me to Merthyr, he'd have to walk all the way back afterwards. But you know what I used to dislike - he would come into the house you know, and my mother would have got 
to bed, and she didn't like young men about the place you see. But he was quite safe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169  enough. But - it made me feel u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
ncom - I didn't have a sister that I could share you see. Because they had all got married. Mm. But - but he had - he had a house - he had it
 all done out for me. Papered by a - proper - decorator you know. And - all furnished ready. So that I - my married life was started in a very nice way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What were you were telling me before about you worked so hard at home papering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh,
 worked so hard, that - that my back was aching. And I - I didn't feel a bit like going - I had my suit made in Cardiff, the same tailor, it was a blue silk, and - I didn't feel a bit happy somehow, I was so tired you know. I - worn out, and - so we were 
- when we went to the hotel, I was really aching. I said to David, oh my back is aching. I'll - he said, I'll go and get some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 embrocating}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 . And he started rubbing my back and I had this - beautiful nightshift. Oh dear dear dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You'd worked so hard doing your mother's house out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
And do you know - when I went to bed I started crying. Instead of being happy - as I ought to be, I was thinking of my mother you know. I hope these people are not - they'll have no end of fun over this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you live after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh in Dowlas. There were two houses together - a very wealthy Jew lived in one and he owned the other. But wherever I went, there were steps. Isn't it strange. Well these steps, and - the carriage that I had for the first bab
y, well it was nearly - 'cos I used to go up Pant Road you know, for the children to have their - and always put them in the front too see. But - it nearly put paid to every carriage I had. And then - when we bought a house in Penybryn, there were about n
ine steps to go up. And I lost about two thousand on that you see 'cos Tudor said - he said, look, mam, he said, you - come on down, he said, people won't want a house with a lot of old steps, but indeed they went for a very good price you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many years did you live in Dowlas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well Tu - Nina and Tudor were born - in Dowlas. See they were both born there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you move then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We moved then - there was a terrible storm, and I had a little - ni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 ce of mine staying, you know, for
 the weekend, she's married and very well - she's living in Stourbridge, they got an estate and all. Well - we moved down to Penybryn, David bought the house, and - we lived there always ten of course, that was between Dowlas and Merthyr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You stayed there then until you came down into Cardiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How old was your husband when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Should have been. Put forty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was your husband's job when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh a - keeping a - grocers shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He had his own grocers shop then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 His own grocer - oh he'd had it - he had it for years. Before I married him you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he have any other jobs before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, only an assistant you see, like they all do you know, they go - they're apprenticed and then they go as assistants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he do anything afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 After? Only chapel. That was his life really. If there was a gymanfa - he'd forget all about the shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you work at all after marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But if - if our - chief - young lady w
ould be away, she got married to a Canadian while - she was with us, and if she would be away I would go up for the weekends you know, to help out. But - I - I would like to have been in the business because - I think I would have been a great asset, but 
he always told me, no, you get enough to do in the house. Which was quite right of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How do you think your husband felt about his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he was such an easy going man you know. You know, many would be worried about the debts that were out
, belonging to him, but he never worried, as long as - and he wasn't a grabber you know, like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did he like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, I think he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It must have been awful during the thirties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? Terrible, mm. But - he - he was a man that did
n't take worry you know. I remember - I don't know whether this would be of any interest, I remember he was - on a conference with the Grocers Federation, and - he had to go away you know, he had quite an important - job with them, he had to go away, and 
-
 I was - I was supposed to have gone, but in the meantime - Nina had diphtheria. So she was rushed to the hospital. And - I couldn't go you see, that had to be cancelled. Well then we had to have the doctor in, to give Tudor - what do they do when they wa
nt to try and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 Inoculation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
That's right. And - oh I've never felt so miserable in all my life to think that poor old Nina - and I shouldn't go near, only see her through the window you see. And - it left her very week you know. She's - you can'
t say that she's been - a strong girl ever, 'cos she's grown tall you see, and - very conscientious. Now when she would be studying upstairs, she'd come down about nine, she'd be like a sheet. Tudor would go up to the bedroom, perhaps he'd be playing a ga
me on the floor. But you see, he could get there much easier than Nina. It wasn't such an effort for him. But she was very thorough in her work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were saying that your husband had to go away on a conference then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were left then were you with the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Left with the two - well you see I couldn't go. And - oh, it - it was a terrible time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had two children didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They were both born before the end of the first world war weren't they? Do you remember when they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Before the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Didn't Mrs Hughes say she was born in 1915?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She would know better than I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How much younger is Tudor than Nina?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Tudor was fifty - Tudor was fifty-three I think - last - last month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 1920 he was born then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Now - how much is between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Four years. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were the children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well
 - I had a very - I had two doctors really, and they had to - I had a very bad time you know. And these two doctors, they were related, but you know what I can remember best of all, I could smell liquor on them. And - but anyhow I came through it all righ
t. And I'll never forget Miss Walsh that was in the shop, she was like a sister, and then My sister Mrs Rhys came up to stay with me you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you were having Nina did you know what to expect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think I did. I - I - I really don't,
 because, we - you know, we never talked about sex. I must - I must tell you this story but you can't possibly put it down there. What do you call that couch, what other word - different to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What were you saying about Catherine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well Catherine
 was two years younger than me, but we were both children you can say. And - this William Hendry was the son of the Red Lion and they kept cows. And of course - they lived in the world of milk and - milk and honey. Well - one of us going down one day, and
 there was Catherine, with a salmon tin - milking Thomas Handry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But of course she wouldn't think anything of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, she thought - she thought it was - one of the cows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did the person do, who saw her, what did they do then with a situation like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well we - we - we as girls then had to tell her, you mustn't do a thing like that, it isn't nice you know, well there's no harm, mammy does it, she says. Well how things stick to you don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You said you had medical help when you had the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your husband help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, but - he was back and forth from the shop to the house you know, it was - rather a - about ten minutes walk, he was back and fore. A hard worker if anybody was. And she said 
to me, oh Get, she said, I feel bad. She said, I'm sure I've had another baby. Well I looked and I said, oh Anne, your liver's come out. And that's what I went through, and another time - another time I was with her, and her husband - had had flu, and I p
ut you know in - there was no - there was no blankets in those days, and - I took a - I think it was a brick upstairs, when I went up the blooming bed was on fire. Talk about experience. I've had it if anybody has.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When you had Nina how soon would you be out of bed after having the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I would - now, it's a - strange thing, my sister younger than me, she would get over it in a very short time, but she'd never sort of - strengthen, you see, she was wanting to go out you know. I stayed in my bedro
om for a month. And then I got very well you see. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You wouldn't be in bed all that time though would you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long would you be in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And then you'd be in the room a fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you stay in bed all day for the first fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I'd sit up you know. And I - well be - now when Tudor was born and Mary was there, and she'd come in you know, and she'd - perhaps she'd have my hat and fur - on, and she'd be like a guest wi
th Auntie Mary. Oh yes. And Tudor was a lovely she - Nina was very pale and puny and I - oh the Virole that I put - and I'd take her out all beautifully white, the Virole perhaps would fall, and giving her everything to strengthen her. Now with Tudor - he
 was a real bonny child. You know, he looked the picture of health. And oh lovely round face he had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did the family manage while you were in bed, having the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well Mary was there you see. My sister. And the nurse would be coming in ever
y day. She was a very good nurse. You'd - you know - really like one of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would any neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. But - in - where we lived you know - if you want to be snobbish - my neighbours were very - pukka. You were asking me last wee
k - if I knew of a real lady. Do you know, I've been looking back this week, they were all in - very good positions, but I wouldn't say that I would call one of them a lady. You know, they were real - social climbers. And there's a lot of it about today y
o
u know. You see. Big man, six foot three and broad as well. I was making his pyjamas for him, his - flannel shirts, and - I said look James, you've got nieces - younger than I am you know, I said, and you could go and they're in nice positions. And he sai
d
, I like a nice bit of food. That's the answer he gave me. He was with me for three years, he nearly put paid to me, because he had that operation. He went then to Llandilo, to a cousin of his, and he came back and he had this operation, and he never got 
over it. Do you know, it would be nothing for him to come down from upstairs in his birthday suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was he your husband's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Brother. I had him there for - three years, and do you know that - there was a nurse living three doors from us, she
 was a lady housekeeper for one of the Friedmans, Jews you know, they were very wealthy, and - so poor old James, the nurse used to come in every day, and twice a day often, and he had gone so stupid he wouldn't do what you'd ask him to do, and she used t
o
 say, well you know, Mr Davies she said, it's a hospital case this is, and he used to beg me not to let him go. To the hospital. Well he was there and - so - he was - taking his breakfast up, he'd eat it and enjoy it. But I went - I - I said to this nurse
,
 I said, I don't know, I said, he - he seems as if he's - you know, losing control of everything. Oh, she said, I expect he's incontinent. I didn't know much what incontinent was to tell you the truth. And - so - David came home and I said poor old James 
is incontinent. What? What, he said to me. I said - I said - I said, he's incontinent. What do you mean, he said to me. Well, I said, he's shitting all over the place. Well - we've often laughed about that you know. I hope you haven't put that down.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had the baby, when you had Nina and Tudor you said you had a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, a nurse, you know, a nurse came -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long would she come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she'd only come for about ten days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She'd come in every day to see to you would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And to advise me you know. To tell me what to do. Not the - not the advantages they get today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you feed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I fed poor old - Nina on the breast, I'm sure she was half starved. But I used to give her -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you enjoy feeding her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh I loved it. It was lovely. And I thought she was the loveliest child, you know, she wasn't to be compared with Tudor. But she's grown up a lovely girl, thank God for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any difficulties in feeding the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well
 I don't know that I had sufficient milk you know. Because - you now - I think it's much better if you take things coolly isn't it, well I had my mind here, there and everywhere you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If you needed advice who did you ask?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I - I don't
 think I'd ask - I don't think I wanted much advice because - I was sensible enough to know - you see, I wasn't - eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You did mention that the nurse advised you in the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she advised me, yes, what to do and - you know, different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have books then, books to read about it all, you wouldn't in your time I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. I'll tell you what I can remember giving Nina though, was a book - it was in the form of flowers you know, and telling them you know - but of course, they used to hear such a lot in school, even at that time you know. Well we never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If the baby was asleep would you wake it for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I used to feed it regularly you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you wake her up to feed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I expect I would, I'm sure I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If she cried before the normal time would you feed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I used to try and - pacify her you know. I remember - I remember - they were going to chapel one Sunday night, and Nina - was not a very good sleeper, and - I t
hought well now I must train her - and she had just gone to sleep when they were coming back - from chapel. But I had no trouble after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you do if Nina didn't seem hungry as a baby, when you were feeding her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I think - you know ther
e was so many - of these - artificial feeds that you could give. And of course Virole was a great thing. And I'll tell you another thing - I used to give her - for her bowels was manna. You know, you read it in the Bible. Don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long would you let the baby go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I don't know, until I think - until it had had enough I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When did you first give the baby solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - with Nina not so young as - as Tudor. 'Cos she wasn't quite as strong you see. But I used 
to have these rusks and different things. You know, we had the shop you see and - I knew - I was never short of anything like that. But - poor old Tudor, he was - so fond of his tummy, and do you know I'll never forget one - night David had gone to chapel
,
 and - he sort of had a - a slight fit you know. And I remember putting him in a bath of water, and I ran up to a chemist, and he came down and he said you did the right thing. And - I think that I had - overloaded him because I wanted to go to chapel you
 see, and I thought he'd be all right. But - he had had too much you see really. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About how old would they be when they had solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I - I don't think we would give it - as - as - early as they do today you know. Didn't - I was very careful that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About how old would they have been now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh gosh, I don't know, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you remember when you weaned them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I tried to keep - Nina, you know, they said - if you could give it for nine months isn't
 it. But I think that I had to break her before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was it sudden or gradual, the weaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh gradual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the baby mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't have trouble weaning them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you think at that time that it did any harm to a baby to let it cry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - I - I never liked to hear them crying. But - mind, when - when she was a child - going to bed you know - I was determined that I'd - get her to go to bed at a certain time, and that she would sleep you know. 
So - I - I never forget this Sunday night, that I broke her in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was it troublesome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh very. Well I was nearly breaking my heart you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You let her cry you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Mm. Of course they say it isn't so dangerous for a girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You let her cry and she went off to sleep by the time they came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So that would have been about an hour and a quarter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But you never had trouble after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That took some doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. I was breaking my heart downstairs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She was crying all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But it's worth it though. How - how did you manage? How did you manage? Felt that Nina wanted such a lot of sleep somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you punish the children when they were naughty if they were babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Once I punished Nina when she started school. I will never forget it. I - you know - I gave her such a whipping. And I don't think she'll ever forget it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 With a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. My hand. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You never punished them as babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Tudor, did you ever have to punish him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I had more - I had more fights with Tudor - when he started schooling - school you know, because - he was - he wouldn't - settle down, and he was so capable you know
. You know, he had it in him, poor old Tudor, and he swears now that I used to put him to wash the scullery floor. He - he wouldn't mind telling you if he was here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't though did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he get them to go to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well no, because I used to put them to bed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he got up to attend to them during the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I don't think - I - we - we were very lucky that way, we didn't have much trouble. Mind the biggest shock I had was when Nina had diphtheria. And of course, I've had shocks since then too. When - when they brought }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he take the babies out when they were little without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But we - well you know - it's a bit awkward - when a man is that age, isn't it. Yes. Well now, we used to g
o round - I can remember then the snow would be - we'd go for a nice country walk you know, but we were not very long before we had a car see. And then it was much easier. 'Cos I used to get very tired going up Pant Road you know, and it was very monotono
us but the air was beautiful. Yes. Well of course I used to go for the child's sake really. And do you know - I had - girls coming in to help you know, they were not much good you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the housekeeping in those days before 1919? Before the e
nd of the first war, just after the end of the first world war? Did you know what your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh well - I - I don't think I did really. Mind - I don't think - he wasn't one to hide anything like that you know. But I remember - you know you'r
e a bit shy when you get married first aren't you, and we had the shop you see, and of course I was never short of money when I was at - when I was - home, because I'd been earning it. And - he said to me, how much - how much do you want now Getta, he sai
d
 to me, to keep a - and we took seven pound. Well of course I'd have all the groceries - sent, and then we'd order the meat, with - the butcher, he was another tradesman, well that would leave the bill go up to twelve and fifteen pounds for meat. Well of 
c
ourse I didn't have to face it, but I didn't like it though. I would rather pay. But anyhow if I'd go to Cardiff - I - I remember going to Cardiff with Catherine - and - I think I had about twelve pounds, you know you could buy a coat then - for less than
 
twelve couldn't you. So we went, and there was a lovely seal coat in Antony's in the window. With fur round the bottom, fur round the sleeves and a fur collar. I said to Catherine, oh I like that. And she said, why don't you have it girl? OH no, I said - 
I've only got - I've only got twelve pounds I said. Go on girl, have it she said, David won't say anything. I put the twelve pound deposit on it and I didn't know how to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And - he was waiting for me now - in Car - in - 171,
 the High Street in - in Catherine's house you see. And - well if he knew I was telling you all this - and - oh I said, I don't know how to tell him. And - so we came home, I think we had a bit of supper there and we came home and - I told him. He wrote a
 cheque without murmuring. And that was the first fur coat I had. I'd given Nina a beauty, that I - paid for - well, I - I could have bought a cottage for what I gave for it. Because I gave my black - broad tail with it you know, but she's had it made }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6818991\charrsid7633169  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 quarter you know, and she looks quite nice in it. Well what do I want, I've got another one upstairs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It's nice for her to use it isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm. Yes. It's a Russian Kolinsky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you discuss with your husband how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - I used to tell him at the end you know - it wouldn't be bad now if I put so and so - bought certificates for the children, and that's how I started for the children you see, and - he was quite agreeable, you know, if I would - suggest anything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was rather different, you didn't have housekeeping as an ordinary woman because you had the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, no. But - but if I went to Cardiff you know - it'd be nothing for me to have twenty pounds now to go you know. Oh he was a won - nothin
g mean about him as long as I wasn't ex - well he knew I wasn't extravagant you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many rooms were there in the house at Penybryn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we had a kitchen, as scullery a large dining room, and that was downstairs. The dining room you could m
ake into two you know, and I had it all carpeted out beautifully, well he did it because - these Friedmans owned the house, and they were - furnishers as well you see. Oh lot of the stuff went to Fowlers you know when I came down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh upstairs, well let me see, it was a - a very - compact house you know. There were four bedrooms. And a bathroom. Oh and - and do you know - when those children were small - Idwil Jones came to us as a minister in Port Morlais, and he was very unl
ucky - as regards his - digs you know, so I said to him, wait until Tudor - wait until - no, wait until I've done my spring cleaning, and you can come here until you get something, I said, to suit you. He didn't wait for me to start my spring cleaning. He
 
was there for nine months and I never charged him a penny. But you see I haven't lost by it have I? And - but what I was very annoyed was - he could have given the children a very nice present. Because I used to do his washing and all you know. And well f
e
d because you see we kept a grocers shop. Well then Victor Griffiths, Peter Hughes Griffiths's brother was coming to Herman. Do you know he wouldn't go to stay with one of his members. Because he was friendly with Eidwil, and no doubt Eidwil said - talk M
r
s Davies into it, so Da - I said to David I said, oh I can never do it, I said to him. I - I can never do it, and I said, and why should I? Well it's up to you, he said. He wouldn't take no for an answer, and how much do you think I charged him for everyt
hing. A pound a week. And he was there until he got married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About a year and a half. So I've done my bit for the preachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't have any other relatives or lodgers ever living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Only my brother-in-law.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Mm? Yes, I used to have - Beattie, she started with my sister, and then she came with me, a nice old girl but - not very intelligent you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would she do, would she live in or was she daily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she'd go home to sleep, 'cos her - her mother was not very far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
And then I had some dailies there. But you know - you couldn't trust them. They would take - my handkerchiefs, sugar - you know, if I went over to 
the shop, I didn't know what would - had gone. But mind there were very good - girls, some of our customers now - used to tell David - they would work in a public house - perhaps they'd have about sixteen shillings a month, and they'd be scrubbing floors,
 and wouldn't have time even to go and pie - buy a pair of shoes. They used to tell my husband you know. Some of our customers they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the girl you had, Beattie, what would she have to do, would she clean or would she look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't have anybody to look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. But - I - I had a girl from Abercaned, Maggie by name. Oh dear dear she was an awful girl. She was supposed to look after them. But do you know when I'd go back from th
e - if I'd go back from the shop, now - this was during the time when David was away again, with some conference or other, and - she would - she wouldn't have - have - risen the ashes even. She'd be reading all the time. Novels. And she - I see her now an
d she's all gush, when I see her you know, and she's grown quite a nice girl.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What hours would the girls work with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they'd go quite early you know. They'd go - between half past four and five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What time would they come in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they come on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, not usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh Saturday they'd come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 All day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you call the girls, by their name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh by their name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes ma'am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 M'am - they used to say you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the washing, would it be done at home or would you send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 At home. All - Never sent a sheet out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would do the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I would. Mm. And not easy like it is today. I suppose you've got a modern machine have you? One like Nina's is it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Clothes when you were married, would you make clothes for Nina and Tudor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Everything. I'll never forget the suit I made for Tudor. Yes, I used to 
try and I was never extravagant you know, perhaps I oughtn't to say it, but I couldn't - I couldn't waste you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were brought up like that you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you mend clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Mr Davies, would he do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh no. He - because we had one headmaster, Mr Pagh, he would do knitting you know. Well there was nothing like that about David. If there - if he liked anything it was music. He was very fond of music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about clothes for you and your husband and the children, would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we'd - sometimes come to Cardiff. Or - perhaps got to Hereford. Yes. My sister and I would go, the youngest one, because - Mary w
as a little bit tighter than - she was, because Catherine never sewed in her life you know, 'cos he was a - in a very nice position, and had a house going with the job you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - really when we needed them you know. Never short then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, come and see my wardrobe. And there's my poor old feet are bad you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when you had the children small and you were married, where would you get your shoes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd go to the best boot - W.R. Williams, Marthryr - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well always when we needed them, and not - and perhaps oftener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your husband, would he help you with jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
He would never carve. How do your husband? Oh. I think now Tudor's a wonderful carver. He's a beautiful - but - but you know, Your whet never carves. Mm. I think it's - and Tudor's a beautiful carver, but - my husband, although - he'
d cut up - sides of bacon, but he would never carve. He'd sharpen the knife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had to carve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I don't know. Isn't it strange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he ever help you in the house with cooking or cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he'd help me to wipe up. Never with cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Ye - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, well he had the shop you see and I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the fires, who would do the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I would always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we always had a man. Because it was - I couldn't be bothered you see and the rooms were very high you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about repairs to the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I had enough decorating before I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Repairs? If the house wanted a repair done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh it have - it's a strange thing, we'd have a little fellow by the name of Pugh, from Pendaren, but you know he did a job for my husband, and he did our bay and did something else, and he charged us a hundred and f
ifty pounds. But you know it was after the war, and he was very unlucky with his men, so we had to pay for their faults, and he was very annoyed, and his son now - is one of the personnel in the BBC in Birmingham, isn't it strange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about any improvements to the house? Would your husband do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh nothing. He would never bother - he'd cut the lawn, but if he'd be doing the lawn on a Thursday afternoon so many people used to pass - and - and they would have a chat, of course the lawn wouldn't be finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about helping you with the children? Would he ever dress the children or undress them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Bath them,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, as a rule you see - when you're in business like that there are some meetings or other - nearly every 
night, Chamber of Trade, or - there was something - continually. So that - he wasn't really in when I was putting them to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he ever read aloud to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I used to do that all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he look after the children when you were out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, he'd do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any regular household tasks that the children had to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. They had to do - do yours? Do they? Oh they do that, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Nina and Tudor have any particular jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well - wash up or something, and - and fair play for Nina now - she would - when she was old enough you know, she would - if I had - perhaps I'd been makin
g something for them, well I couldn't do everything, and she would dust down upstairs you know. She was a good little girl like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What time would the children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they would never be late, but - mind when they'd be studying, Nina w
ould come down from upstairs about nine, and she would have a light supper and then she'd go to bed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when they were small children, what time did you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh round about - before seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they go to bed themselves or would you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well when they were small I'd take them up you know and tell them a little story.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You would, not your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the children share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. They had a - a single bed. And I gave that single bed to - Eidwel Jones our minister's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did they share the bedroom when they were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They had a bedroom each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your family, how did you sleep, Nina had a bedroom and Tudor had a bedroom and you and Mrs Davies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, and then we had a spare room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the bathroom, you had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would they bath,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would the children bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - usually every night, when they were small you know. Well Lisa nearly lives in the bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When did the children have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, regularly you know. If they were - soiled now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about meals then, where were the meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh in the - in the - living room. I wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you ever eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I wouldn't - I wouldn't put - for ordinary meals - in the dining room. You know, unless it was something special. 'Cos was such a big room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you call something special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well,
 say now somebody was - coming you know, some - visitors or things like that. Well the children would usually be in bed you know. When they were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where did you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I - in the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I had a gas cooker. But I had a range too, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you use that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes - not often though, 'cos you know, you wanted such a huge fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course we'd all - we'd always have it - in the morning now - in time for the children to go to school. Of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Mr Davies have it with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. But he would - he wouldn't be in a hurry to go over to the shop you know. But - Tudor was very - you know, breakfast time now - he wouldn't want h
alf his - what I'd prepare for him, because - it's nearly always a cooked breakfast, and - do you know who used to come and finish it? Now you'd be surprised. I don't know whether you've heard of - was it Professor Young, Aberystwyth, now he had a sister 
Mrs - oh - she lived - she lived - we lived up here and they lived down there, and those boys - they're in Harley Street, he used to come and - finish Tudor's breakfast, 'cos she wasn't much of a wife you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He used to come and call for Tudor did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes, he'd come and call and he'd finish Tudor's breakfast. They were going to the County School, and do you know - when there was an exam on - Musgrove, now they're - they're Harley Street today, well do you know that - and she was a - I think she 
was a B.A. but if those children were backward in anything, she'd have them coached straight away, in Latin or anything like that, and this boy, I can't remember his name, used to go to the exam and he'd have an old - empty - pocket watch, and he'd have -
 bits and pieces in there you know to - and Tudor said - perhaps there wasn't one question - asked - but as a rule she'd have him - coached straight away, and look where they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What sort of food would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd have
 - if it was cold we'd have - you know - either quaker oats or - you know, some cereal, and then - usually bacon and eggs. Because of course we were in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh tea, never coffee. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have anything different on certain days, like Sunday for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about lunch time now, what was the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have dinner midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Every day. Every day, hot dinner, yes. It turns on me sometimes. And Nina cam
e back last night and she said to me - now what would you like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about dinner hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would be there, would your husband come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. He'd come home from the shop. And as a rule he'd drop off to sleep, and - perhaps he 
wouldn't go to the shop until it was about closing time. He was very cool you know, nothing - bothered him much. And of course, it was something new for him to have a home you see. 'Cos he'd been in digs you know, and - well really and truly do you know -
 
she was a spinster, and when we went to London, I forgot to tell you this, the first thing - we had to go into - what's the name, there's a shop in Cardiff - to buy candies for him. Well he didn't like to tell me before you see. Mm. 'Cos his mother had di
e
d - he took me to see his mother you know before we were married. His - do you know, his - his brother - your husband perhaps - old J.T. Richards was one of the first solicitors in Cardiff and he was a Mayor of Cardiff, and he had his office - above Halls
 
there, and Marjorie's daughter was the only - the first lady solicitor to pass, and James married - Richards's sister. The - my brother-in-law that died in our house. And - if ever he married an old maid. He didn't marry until he was retired. In the polic
e force he was you know. He didn't marry until he - was retired. But oh - come in. Now she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you have for midday meals in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, you ought to ask Tudor that. He loved his tummy. We'd always have a good meal you know. Mind some
times it would vary, sometimes - oh - what was it old Tudor used to love now? We used to have spare rib, you know, we used to have that lovely pork, without - do you remember the grocers used to keep it. And we'd have a nice piece of that. And - do you kn
ow David never sent - I know a grocer in Dowlas used to send - scraps home. But he never - if - if ever we had a nice piece of ham it was always a nice corner piece. Always had the best. So we - we've had good living always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have another meal then again, would you have tea or would you have an evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
We - we - we'd have - tea, but if - if the children were home we'd have to have tea you see, but then - David would like something savoury you know when he'd come home. He -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Mr Davies be there for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. He'd have his tea in the shop you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about in the evening? Would the children have a meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well Tudor would sniffle, he could - he - he wouldn't go far if there was something savoury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would they have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - we used to have - cider. You know, we'd have these little bottles of cider. Oh it was delicious. But the children wouldn't drink it. They would have some - you know, pop or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think I did - then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I'd make and bottled - bottled everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Though you had the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Though you had the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we were not - I've done more pickling since I'm here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about wine, would you make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes, elderberry wine. I - do you know, before - before Nina got married - I paid a shilling a pound for rhubarb, you know, it was very scarce, it was during the war. 
And I put it in the - we had a - we were living in Penybryn now, and there was an outside pantry, and I had a big pan, I don't know what it didn't cost me for sugar and all, I got up one Sunday morning - our - that pantry was like a brewery. It had burst.
 I only saved about three bottles. And that's what we had for Nina's wedding.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you make any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Yes I did try - making - small beer out of herbs you know. Diod faen. Do you make any now? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Medicines, would you make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh bottled fruit, I - well you know it was - the jars that I left behind. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never bottled vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you grow your own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You'd buy them, you had the shop of course, did you sell everything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about tinned vegetables or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh gosh - our customers - we knew what they wanted when they gave their order, it was always - peas, you know, thos
e dried peas. They were Irish most of them. And you could tell - and perhaps - that much of the country would be their order you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you keep any livestock, any pigs or hens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many times a week did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh nearly every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have any extra meat from poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 From what? In the country I used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But not after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Well we didn't like rabbit much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You never went short of course because you had the business didn't you, you were never short of food or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your husband need to have larger helpings of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh he was a good eater. He enjoyed his food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the children at the table, were they allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes - well - poor old Tudor, I remember we had - W.N. Jones, he died about a fortnight ago - he - happened to be in our house having dinner this - particular Sunda
y, I think you know they used - they'd ask me to keep the month for I don't know how many people, and - old Tudor would have a good dinner, and - I'd say - will you have some more Tud? Do you know, he'd say, a little of everything mammy please. And old W.
M. used to laugh. Mm. He's always been a good eater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were they allowed to talk during the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh yes. As a rule - I remember we had a - another little minister there to dinner, and the children were asking him - how do you study? When they were younger you know. And he was rather a studious minister. How do you study, they said to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did he say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I forget what he told them, you - but you'll stick yours too from Kevin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could the children choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I didn't have much trouble that way. Perhaps Nina would be more - fidgety than Tudor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was your attitude if they left something on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Gosh - ask them now what's there ought to 'cos I - I - always leaving. You know, when you get older you don't want a lot do you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When the children left anything what did you feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I used to be a bit worried if they'd leave it, you know, I'd think well - something must be wrong with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the children wait until things on the table were offered to them, like the salt, or could they ask for the salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they'd ask. Because we did have a cat, and I'll never forget this - David was away, some conference or
 other, and I had to nip over to the shop you know, and I left the house and - when I came back the cat was in the oven, dead. It -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What had happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It had got - it was a range you see, in the kitchen, and no doubt the kitchen was warm. And - 
and that - I must tell you, that cat - we had gone, I forget where we went to Swansea or Cardiff, and we had - had that kitten given me, and I'd a barberry mack on, and I was nursing the cat, and indeed if it didn't wet all over my barberry. Oh dear.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the children, were they allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. We'd had enough of that in my - early days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or did they have to eat what you put?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh a
lways a cooked meal, and especially Tudor, I remember that we had a minister staying with us on one Sunday, and - Tudor was a good eater you know, and he said - will you have more Tudor. Yes a little of everything mammy please. And this minister was laugh
ing you know, because he'd said that. Always fond of his tummy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did they have to hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I used to try and teach them the - you know, table manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they have to sit in a certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were they allowed to bring toys to the table, or a book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I never remember - I - they were not studious enough for that I don't think, but I remember very well we had a - we had another minister, a Mr Hughes, quite a learned sort of man, and 
I remember them asking him, how do you study? Because you see - mm. They - you know, they wanted to know the proper way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When did they leave the table after having a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - we never used to have grace you know. No. Not even when I had - Eidwel there. Never had grade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they get up, would they wait for you all to finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no, they could go you know. It was a - I tried to make it a real home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they wait until things on the table were offered to them, like the salt, or would they ask for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I - I think I used to see that everything was on the table, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they ask somebody to pass the salt or could they just take it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they - asked to pass it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we were - we were only four you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well all I know is that my husband never carved. Mm. You see, he - he had cut up such a lot of mea
t that I think he was - glad for someone to cut it for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you see you sat at the same place at the table always, and Mrs Davies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Usually, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How would you serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I would put the - their meal and then they could help themselves to vegetables you know, and gravy and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You put the meat out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But you'd have them in tureens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about when the children were too young to feed themselves? What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well of course I used to try and feed them you know, I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You would do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Try and see that - oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would they sit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I would sit - well I'd have to sit at the table because you see I'd have the child - you mean when they were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Before they could sit up at the table themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You would hold the child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. I had everything - that I needed. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So they'd sit in a high chair until they were old enough to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way or a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I always felt there was a right way. Yes. I always felt that. 'Cos 
I often feel now - that today - I find some of the parents, that they're bringing them up the wrong way, to my way of thinking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What do you think is the wrong way then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I - I don't quite approve - of a parent allowing - the child - to - h
ave all the freedom you know to choose for themselves, I think that you - they want to be guided more, but - I always think of D.R. Thomas, Merthyr, you know, the minister. Now he allowed his children you see, to do just as they liked, they were little te
r
rors on the road. Well now those - I don't know where they are, they went in for music I think. And - I think they're abroad, and even the little daughter, Rianon, a lovely little girl, how she got married you see, and went away you know. She's in London.
 But I haven't seen D.R. to ask him - any questions since he left Merthyr you see because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you feel when you were bringing up Tudor and Nina?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I tried to bring them up - you know - to have good manners, and do you know - what I'm most
 pleased about, even the mistress at the school said, we've never taught two nicer children. Well that was a compliment wasn't it, and even now you know - Merthyr people say, oh well you've got two lovely children. Well you feel very pleased, although the
 children don't want to hear it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I think - I think he left it really to me you see now - for instance he'd be in the shop, and then he'd have a meeting perhaps afte
rwards, well our kitchen table would be nothing but books, and I hadn't gone further than the - than elementary school, but you know I used to try - to teach them and - and old Tudor would say, mammy, I've got an essay to write, give me some ideas. And I'
d
 give him some ideas, but he'd always - he'd always end up - and the sky was overcast. And today you know, he's a wonderful letter writer. But - but you now, he can't do - for his children, like I used to do for him, they - they're different aren't they. 
And - I tell - I used to say, well never mind Tudor, what you've lost on the roundabouts you must - make up on the swings, and hitch your wagon to the star, they' got all those sayings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever talk about how to bring up the children you're your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, because - my - my sister next to me didn't have any children, and my youngest sister - well Glyn is in the home now. She was hop
eless I think as a mother. You know, she - as long as she had a smart - hat, and a smart rig out, I - she didn't used to seem to sacrifice somehow. It is a - it is a - a labour of sacrifice isn't it I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You have to give time to them don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Mm? Oh - I never - no. Now Catherine used to love to go to town you know, and she'd take the child with her. Well now I never did, I'd take them out to the country you know in the carriage, and keep them at their bedtime. Strict about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was your mother alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you see her often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 As often as I could because you see - with the children I would have to walk down to Merthyr and it was all a hill up. Back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How often would you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I'd try and see her once a week at least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I don't think so. No. I - you see - somehow or other - I - I don't know whether the seventh child has got more to do - than the others, but 
I seemed to be a sort of - a help to them all. Do you understand? Now Mary wasn't much good you know. You know, I remember - I used to do the cooking when I was - when I was young you know, and I remember Christmas time, we would have the - turkey down th
e
 cellar, in front of the fire, cooking, and you - would be in a bath of perspiration, and Mary would make the sauce, and she said - my mother would say, well - Mary is no cook. Instead of putting sugar she'd put salt. You know. But she - she came. She mar
ried an architect and she came a very good wife. Well she was more of a social worker. She had no children, and she was on the hospital committee, on this that and the other, and - you know, she used to write - many of - of - Tom's addresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother have the same ideas on how to bring up children as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well we were brought up quite strictly, but you see - she didn't have the facilities - where - as we - the same as we had, and - and she didn't have the - money either.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your mother-in-law, was your mother-in-law alive when you had the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh, I saw her - David took me to see her before we were married, they - she lived at Llandilo. And she was a dear old soul, and - of course David was the - youngest son yo
u see, and - then - I went to see her again after we were married. And she was very nice. But she died soon after - no, no, she died - I remember going to the station to see him off, to bury his mother. So I - she didn't bother me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She was dead when you had the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, she was dead. She was very nice though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What were some of the things you felt you ought to do you're your children? You said you helped them with their school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I did a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you really feel you should do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Do you know, my sister used to come our house and she used to say - do you know Getta, she said, I envy you because she said - you are really - educating yourself, you know, by - helping them. Well I alwa
ys wanted them to be clean, and nicely dressed you know. Of course the suit that I made Tudor, oh - well - his tie was one side and he was such a pretty old kid. And - he got older and the girls used to come on to me and used to say, oh Mrs Davies, ask Tu
d
or to come to the school party. Tudor didn't want to bother with girls. And - I used to say, you ought to go Tudor. Well Mary and I went down - to choose a - he wanted the trousers nineteen inches round the bottom. Never went to the party, the boys and he
 went to the party and helped themselves - to some cakes and things, and that's the end of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about affection, would you show them affection or would they show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Oh I - I used to worship that Nina. And of course - Nina 
was christened at home you see, the minister came because I was - but Tudor now, David couldn't come down to the - we went to the site in Merthyre, and - I took him down, and do you know, some of the people said, he's a handsomest child I've ever seen. Of
 course he wasn't - he - he was - really older than he should have been. But he was a plump sort of boy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, I was always prepared to put - poor old Nina when she was studying - oh s
he'd go upstairs you know, and she'd - she'd work until nine o'clock then she'd come down, she'd be like a sheet. I never had to tell her. Tudor would go upstairs, I'd go up, he was playing on the floor. Some sort of game. Did you have that? But you see, 
he didn't need a lot of studying. Because - he - when the exam - when the result of the exam came out, he met Mr Pugh the headmaster and he said, Tudor, you can go to any university, he said, you've got the five subjects, and only the five he had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He had the right ones though, how did you want the children to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh I wanted them to respect me, and they did too. They do now you know. I think I've had a bit more cheek with Nina - you know, we argue with things, but - I don't know -
 I fancy that the boys seem - well I don't know, old Tudor's - seems - well even Marjorie said, when they got married first - there seems to be much - closer tie between you and your mother than there was between her brother and her mother you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no, never. Unless - mind you when they're older they would argue perhaps, but not when they were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I think chapel more than - more than anything. And Sunday school you know and Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you tell them that they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't remember saying that. But I - I don't think they used to - I - I - I nev
er can - I would never complain about Tudor or that they were - disagreeable with anybody you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Well you know when they go to - when - do you mean now when they go to 
- to the secondary school? Well - you see - I used to try and - advise Nina you know, who to be friendly with, because - but she never - she would always - the bottom dog with Nina always, she'd always be nice to them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What was it you didn't like about the ones, would you discourage her from going with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well it was no good because now - there's a little girl, she lives in Sully now - and Nina tells me that she's got such an accent, that - you could almost cut it. She's l
iving in Sully and she's - she was a Catholic girl, and she lived you know - in a - a little cottage, and Nina used to call for her on Saturday morning, and she said, oh mammy, she said, you can't see poor old Molly for black lead. You know, she'd be tryi
n
g to clean. They were Catholic - Catholic family, but she was quite a nice girl, but Nina said she went to - spend a holiday with them, married very well. She - she didn't go to college but she went to London as a receptionist, and that's where she met th
i
s man. And Nina was there spending a holiday, she said she never had such a miserable time in the life. Molly was quarrelling with this - man, and she said, and he was really such a nice boy. So I don't know what state is on - she's got - one or two child
ren, the - they're married anyhow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If Nina or Tudor did something you disapproved of what would happen? You did mention earlier that you gave Nina a smacking once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. But Tudor - if I - if I'd ask Tudor, now - Tu, you wash the dish - you wipe 
the dishes now for me, there was always a bit of - of a - you know - didn't want to do it, but - if he - if he was here now he'd swear to you that he used to wash the scullery. I can't remember him doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would he always wipe up for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, he'd have to do what I'd tell him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you do if he misbehaved, would you ever punish him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I'd give him - I suppose I'd give him a knock but I would never punish, you know, I could never whip him or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You'd just give him a smack would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Nina, only the once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Only once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your husband, would he ever punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. Never. Never. I don't think that he put a hand near them ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no, I - 'cos we - you see - somehow or other - David was - not educated but 
he was - a natural gentleman. You know, if he'd get up in chapel - he wasn't one to getup often, but - you could tell, people used to listen you know, when he was in the big seat talking. 'Cos he - he wasn't a - he wasn't a man that wanted to show himself
 ignorant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't work at all after you had the children did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. Only at home. OH - do you know Mrs - Preece, before Nina was born - I tucked and balanced these lace - her robes, I had - beautiful things for her. And I gave one of them t
o one of our missioners, she was - expecting - Doctor John Williams's wife, and she was expecting a baby and she - happened to call in our house and I said, look, I've got a robe here, I said, you're quite - balanced with lace and tucks, beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were busy like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When the children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Don't talk to me about a birthday, I gave them a birthday party in Penybryn, and Marjery, my daughter-in-law she was a little girl, 
but they lived in Pant you see. Good way off. And - her brother came, no, Marjory came, and - the - quite a lot of the little children there, and on top of our dresser in the kitchen there was a cigar, and it had - like a gold paper round it you know, you
 would think it was an ornament. Do you know those children - you'd hardly believe it, they climbed up, they got all my dresser down. Every dish. I've never seen such a mess. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I was shocked. I think we did - we were able to claim something from insurance you know. But nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They broke things did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm? They were smashed to bits. The - the dresser fell you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Nobody was hurt though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But I'll never forget that. That was a - that was one birthday party anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you give a birthday party every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No, I don't think - no, not every year. Now my neighbour next door - Canton the solicitor he was, and they had two daughters, but - never a birthday party. Never. But - do you know
 poor Mrs Canton, she died, she had - Paggets disease of the hip. Well I could write a book, and - Dorothy had got married, she's divorced.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your children have presents on their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, but not like they do today you know. Not mo
ney. You know. Like today, if you give - two or three pounds - they don't think much of it do they. For they - well you'd know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would they have something different to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they'd have a proper - jellies and all the rest of it. Well today I he
ar Marjorie say if you put crisps and - something else on the table - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Can you remember anything you did with your husband and the children on Christmas Day? What would - Christmas Day be like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I can remember - well one Christmas Day and the
 snow was on the ground and I can - and do you know - David wasn't a young bride you see. And we took the children for a walk right round - the country you know. And back. Well - after that I think we had a car. So it was easier. It was much easier you kn
ow. But it was a beautiful walk. And you know, crisp. We don't get that weather here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were higher there you see weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh it was beautiful, up - round Ponsahn you know and back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well the first - music - well - we had a piano. Well I don't know where it would go in here. Huge. And we - we were offered a hundred pounds for it, I think we had to give it away at the end. It was so big, but - a beautiful - strung beautifully you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who played it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well let me see now, did I give - not one of them very musical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did any of you play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 David was rather fond of playing hymns you know. He took a few lessons - earlier on. He was very - he knew every 
- tune, you know, he - he knew every tune by its name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did any of you sing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Only - in chapel, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever make music together in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were there books, newspapers or magazines in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Plenty of books, any amount. The - bookcase was full of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. The - Western Mail of course, and the Merthyr Express.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Well of course the - I don't think there were quite as popular - in those days y
ou see as they are today. You know, it was - would be - more like - these little picture books for children and - that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you get the books from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh from our bookseller you - from the - newsagent you know, they would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I did once. We had a very good library in Merthyr you know. Gefartha Castle there's - beautiful, you - have you ever been to Gefartha Castle? Well you see - Crawshaw build that you see. And - from some of the windows h
e could see his works. And it was a beautiful Castle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It's in a park now isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
A park, you ought to go and see it. Well now you know - if you go up - by bus to Brecon to - up to the - park gates, you'll see those gates, now our councillors h
ave been trying - to - to do away with those gates, in order - that the children - could go up by bus - and - go up the drive you know. There was writing about that in the Merthyr Express, continually - only about a month ago. But there - people wrote fro
m Canada, Australia, you know, old Merthyr people, and saying what a sin it would be to do away with those gates, that the workmanship was wonderful. And of course - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I noticed the gates as you come along the Brecon road in the car you pass it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That's right. Yes. Well, they're majestic aren't they? Mm. And of course the gardens used to be beautiful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever read aloud to each other, you and Mr Davies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you read aloud to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Mr Davies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Not often. And we'd teach them - verses of course when they were small you see. You know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would Mr Davies teach them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Oh that Tudor, he - you would laugh if you heard him reciting his Welsh verses. And poor old Marjorie, m
ountain stream, sparkling pebbles, that's about all she knows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Were the children taken out visiting, neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You mentioned that you took them down to see your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go at all anywhere else? With the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh we'd take them to Gefartha Park you know on a - a - there was a big - fet every year with the hospital committee. And Auntie May was a big woman in that. Well we would take them there, and I'll never forget my mother 
knitted - a cardigan for - in beautiful Jaegar wool, for - Tudor and - Nina, the same, and - she couldn't do the armholes you know, she'd do the plain part but I would have to - tell her how to go on, and they were beautiful, do you know I had one under m
y arm, we lost it in the park. Never found it after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about shopping, would you take the children shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, not unless - there was something that they - wanted you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would go with them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 To do - well they never went
 shopping really. Well we had the shop and - Tudor used to spend a lot of his time round the shop, because there was lots of things that - we never lived on the premises you see. 'Cos - they wanted it for - a store room you know and during the - war you k
now you had to stock such a lot. I remember - them queuing up for bread, it was nearly a mile long. You know, during the war.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did the children ever go out with Mr Davies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. They loved their father. He - he'd nev
er say a cross word to them. But he expected them - to do well - in their exams mind. But you see he hadn't - helped in any way now - well I don't think he had the time - really. Mm. And you see, he - he was really quite important in - in the Chamber of T
rade and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about on the Bank Holidays, what would you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh, we'd try and arrange some - we had the car then, we could go - we went, I remember going to - see my nephew in Chester one - holiday. And - we had a wonderful
 time. Oh dear dear dear. Poor old Dorothy's never - he never had to try the test you see. They didn't in those days. And we were going through now one of the places as we were going in - to Chester, and we nearly knocked a policeman down, the policeman t
urned round and he said, what the - what the hell are you trying to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 There was nothing much on the road then was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. But Horace - my nephew, he couldn't drive, but he learnt to drive - on our car. And then Tudor you see when he was - wh
en he started in the bank, they put him in Cambridge. And we used to go there, and we'd spend - the best part of a month. My sister would come with us, Mrs Rhys, well I've never enjoyed anything as much, but the first time we went - we had to go round loo
k
ing for digs for Tudor. He was - he said - she's a - she's an old lady he said, and she's an old hypocrite. That's what he used to call this woman. She'd go - she'd go to church on Sunday morning and perhaps she'd have four or five men in the house, and s
h
e wouldn't bother about - cooking - dinner, but she'd give them these old pies and things, well he had - hadn't been used to it. He couldn't bear being there. And we tried to get digs and it was - sweltering weather. Very hot. But anyhow - after he'd been
 there a couple of years we had a chat with the manager, and - decided we'd like him to come nearer home. And where do you think they put him then? Mountain Ash. But he wasn't there long you know, he changed about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever go away for a holiday when the children were young?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh we were - spent - every - every summer - we used to go to Llanroted for a month. And - David would come home then, like on a Thursday afternoon, for the Friday you see, and then he'd come away - on a Saturday again. That's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He just came home for the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And we met such nice people when we were there, 'cos - the Cloth Hall you know is a noted place to stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why did you choose to go to Llanupted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well I don't know how we started going ther
e, but we enjoyed it so much - that - we have been to - to - when the children were small, I was only telling Nina yesterday, we went to Cardigan - what's the name of the place now in Cardigan, the lovely little seaport. Newquay. We spent a lovely holiday
 there. And met some nice people from Dowlas that we didn't know before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You used to go every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh every year for a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you do when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well we'd go down to the lake, you know and - oh we had so - no end of fun. And such a lot -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever have a little part time job or any means of earning regular money while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your first job now when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well, I went to learn my
 trade you see. I went - I went first of all - to the Manchester House. That was one of our biggest - drapers shops you know. And I wasn't there long before - I was an improver. And I was having two and six a week. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you have when you started first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Two and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you think that was fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - it was what they were paying you see in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What hours did you work for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Used to go at nine in the morning. And we'd come home to 
have lunch. And then we'd finish at - I think it was about - oh do you know, I can't remember whether it was six or seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did we work on Saturday? Yes, we worked on Saturday too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would it be all day on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When would you have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh never on Sunday. We never did - even when we had our own business we never worked on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh that wasn't heard of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you get the job in Manchester House, how did you hear of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I suppose they thought that I was quite good you now, and they offered it to me. Well I went from there then to - Artie Jones's, that was a little bit higher again you know, the
 - the trade was better. Well I didn't have any more money, half a crown. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you hear of that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh they were - they were always prepared to take improvers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long were you at Manchester House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I don't think I was there six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And then you went to R.T. Jones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 The same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you feel it was a fair wage there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pay what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I suppose we tho
ught it was wonderful you see, in those days. And then when I left R.T's - there was a Miss Price there. She was a - a bodice hand you see, you know a bodice hand had - an - an improver, and the head was from - Germany, she was very clever. But very fond 
o
f the drink. But she was a really good head. And Miss Price now, she was a very good looking girl, and - you know, I had - I was very fond of her, so she said - look Miss Harper she called me, because there were so many Miss Davies', Miss Harper she said,
 
I'm going to start a business in Swansea. And, she said, would you be prepared to come? I was full of it. I said to my mother - oh - she said - in Welsh, you don't want to go there, she said. Four shillings a week she was offering me. And living in. Oh, I
 
said, let me go. I - I had my hair down my back you know, and - the - the greatest friends I ever met - were the Mendis's family. They were going to Trinity and I was friendly with the two girls. And Mrs - Mendis used to say, Getta, she said, you come her
e whenever you want to, and she said I think Getta'll marry a preacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You went to chapel there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Regularly. I had a lot of fun with boys you know. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh, about - between seventeen and eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So you were in R.T. Jones's a few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 About five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh no, not as long as that. Oh I can't remem - I don't know whether I was as old as that now in Swansea, I can't re - I was only a girl with my hair down my back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did you get on with the other people you worked with in Manchester House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh wonderful. Wonderful. I had a wonderful time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the money you earned then, the half a crown, did you give any of it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I suppose I gave it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You don't know what she spent it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh - it would be really something for us you see. 'Cos she was - she was so wonderful, I was only telling Nina - she gave each of us a set of china
 like that you know - a dozen. Every one of us girls. And she gave us everything when we got married. You know - beds, everything you could think of. And she gave - twenty pounds she gave me and I put it - I put it in Pendaren cinema and my mother said, D
evils work, she said. And I lost it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the work when you started as a little girl in Manchester House and in R.T. Jones, did you like it or did you dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I liked it. You know - you see I didn't have - important things to do. I wasn
't responsible you see. But when I went to Swansea to Miss Price - she was very good looking and she was going - with a very smart - her sweetheart was there you see, he had a salon - hairdressing and in the front was a shop, with Mr - Mr Davies, he had a
n
 outfitters shop, and he used to take me to Sunday school, he was - well - much older than I was, and you know in those days he'd wear a top hat, and - he was related to the Knights, the Doctor Knights Swansea, he was going to - what's the name of that ni
c
e - Congregational chapel in Walters Road? Walters Road I think. Yes. Well - he was such a nice fellow. Well I absolutely fell for him although he was old enough I'm sure to be my father. But he was so nice to me always. And he'd take me as far as Trinity
,
 the old Trinity you know, and then he'd go to his Sunday school. Well I usually used to go back then to the Mendis's to tea you see. Well do you know I've never been so disappointed in anybody as I was in Miss Price. She was deceitful. I - and I was half
 starved there. Everytime I came home I would take tea down to her, and homemade bread and all the rest of it. But I didn't complain to my mother you know, 'cos she didn't want me to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You lived in with Miss Price did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. She had a flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And you did the work in the flat did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. Well - we did it between us, it was only a workroom and a bedroom you see. And then Mrs Jones would usually come up - to have a bit of supper, he'd bring it with him, and Mr Davies would be with him 
as a rule, he - Mr Davies was much more of a gentleman than Mr Jones, never liked Mr Jones, you know, one of these - with monocles and very tall, and - put all his go - goods in the shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were only a young girl weren't you going there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Very young. Very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you go home often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 As often as I could. But I used to enjoy my Sundays down there because of the - the friends I made you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go to chapel all day on Sunday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. All day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Morning, afternoon and evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about, how did you get on with Miss Price?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I never quarrelled with her but I used to see - now we would go to a warehouse you know. Do you know that she wouldn't leave anything alone. She'd - pocket things you
 know. And then - Mr Davies had a shop in front, with ties and all the rest of it. I don't know what she used to take. I was disgusted with her. I didn't stay long after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How long were you there with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 I should think I was there for two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well, she wasn't what I'd call - a first class hand you know. And she didn't have - a lot of - so I couldn't expect much more than four shillings a week could I? But she - she wasn't a clever girl, I wouldn't 
think so. She - she was pretty, and then she - came to live to Rodrue, but I never saw her, when she was down there. I didn't want to see her. Because - you know, I sort of worshipped her before I knew what she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You found she had feet of clay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And I was very disappointed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You had that job because you were working with her in R.T. Jones, how did you - what sort of hours did you work with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh - oh - not - we never worked very late because - she didn't have a great business you know
. And I think - I think really she was there because - Mr Jones was there you see. Mind I - they were - they didn't live in sin or anything like that. Not as far as I know, no, I'm sure of that. He married her afterwards but he died - and - there was a li
t
tle girl there related to Gwynfa Evans, this girl, she used to go out and - get all the burgundy for this head - in - R.T. Jones's, and of course she got very friendly with this Miss Price, because she used to invite her down to her house you see. But - s
he didn't know her deceit like I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What did you do then when you left Miss Price?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh I came home then because - my sister then started you know - we were getting - older of course, and Mary had to leave the higher grade you know, I told you - 
that she had - a - she caught a damp bed. And - and of course we never turned back you see, once we started - plenty of work. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were self-employed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You and your sister ran the dressmaking business didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Bu
t she was the clever one mind, mind I was the one - that did the nice work. But she was the - mm - well she was so clever with cutting out, and designing. But you know if she would have a thing on, you could - catch hold of it and just pull it, because - 
there was no sewing, but - she had the - appearance and the design, she never used a pattern you know. No. But she was - she was a clever writer too you know. She was - she was gifted, there's no mistake about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What hours did you work then in your own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well we'd start in the morning but I - I had to do all the housework as well at home you see. Help with the washing, everything. And most of the cooking. Well poor old Mary, she used to shout from upstairs, Getta, when are you coming up,
 you know, because of course - she missed me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were doing all the dressmaking side of it weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. She -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She saw all the customers you said?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How many girls did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well we had five - w
e could only keep so many you see, so we had to very careful, because we didn't want to be fined, so we had a room up above - and I used to be up there you know with the - with the three girls would be up there, and perhaps Mary'd have five 'cos is a bigg
er room. And then poor old Mary, she'd come down to Cardiff to do - I told you that did I before? She -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She had the training of dressmaking teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And of course she was the only one that passed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You carried on the business while she was doing that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, well - as - as best - as best I could you know. Gethin Lewis's daughter was one. And they were all - moneyed people you see, but - oh -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You said you didn't work on Sunday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. We always went out on Saturday afternoon and Thursday afternoon. Two - we didn't make a slave of - of - of it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about the apprentices you had there, would they have the same hours as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, yes. And they 
used to pay you know, for being apprenticed. Ten and six a - quarter. Well now Mary had that money. I didn't have that. But we used to share half of the making, you see, then if - if she had to buy trimmings - she would have you know, a - a bit of profit 
on that, 'cos - things were trimmed such a lot weren't they. Oh, and - you know, this sequins and all the rest of it. Much more work than today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What would you say you were paid, 'cos it was your own business it's difficult isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You didn't have a wage really did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh no, we used to divide - and of course - if - you know, we didn't charge you know for a lovely costume, we would only charge a pound. Well today it's five or six pounds for making, and a job to get somebody isn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you feel that it was a fair wage you were having then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh yes. Yes. Fair enough because you see - I wasn't sort of full time, but I used to pull my weight you know, when - when I was up in the work room, and on a Friday you know I'
d be pressing downstairs, and our friends would come and see us on Friday night, say we had a tea-party in chapel they'd want their hats trimmed you know. Of course that was all for nothing, we were not charging. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You did say that both of you when you gave up the business would have five hundred pounds each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. Without our stock. You know, our - bottom drawer and top drawer. And that wasn't bad for those days. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But you did have a salary every week did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, we used t
o divide you know, perhaps the customers wouldn't pay - straight away, you know, they'd leave it for a week or a fortnight, some good customers would leave it for more than that, but we knew it was safe you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You haven't had any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
I wanted to be nurse. But - you see my friend went to Middlesbrook and she'd a brother then in a very good position, and she was an orphan, she was my Merthyr friend - chapel friend. And -
 Gwen - she was going to Middles - Middles borough and she said, oh come Getta, she said. My mother said, oh - too far. So - but I think I would have liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you actually serve an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well not much. I didn't serve much of an ap
prenticeship you see. Because - they must have thought that I was pretty good you see. Oh. This is - this frock - this frock I made - oh - years ago, this is a - I pleated this myself. But I - do you know I got no - I - I bought a little frock in - what d
o you call that posh shop in town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you ever belong to a trade union or a professional organisation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We knew nothing at all about it. The first thing I can remember is when Kier Hardy got in for Merthyr. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you feel that there 
were divisions of interest among the workers in those days? Some people say that there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers. Did you feel that? You were training people weren't you to be dressmakers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, but you know - we
 never had - we never had much to do now - with - the colliers you know. Mind, there were some very respectable colliers, but others you see - they didn't try. Well you see it today don't you? I always think God helps those who help themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you feel there was a difference between the ones who had had a training, trained craftspeople and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well of course the poor scavengers in those days, they were scavengers weren't they. Now today you see - here they are with their - hands - gloves on their hands, things have altered so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about life at home after you left school, when you started in Manchester House.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you continue to live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. I think - I think it drew us nearer if anything. Yes. She was still my mother, and a wonderful mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 In what way do you think it drew you nearer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - you know, we were able to help her a little, which was - which is a great joy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about your relationship with your brother and your sisters then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh well one brother - one brother we had you see. And my mother worshipped him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 He was already away wasn't he when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
When he - yes, and he - he was a signalman and then he came back to Merthyr and he was the - inspector on the platform. But of course he made a big mistake you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 It was only you and Mary and Catherine were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Now they were all marri
ed you know. Seven - seven were - happily married, my - nicest sister I had - she had an awful husband. Making money, but mind she was working hard in the shop. And the owners of the shop, now they had got on in the world, the Evans's, Helgerig, Six Bells
 
they called them. Ordinary people but they had their own colliery you see. And - do you know they never - when they come - to the shop to give their order you know, they'd come in their - carriage and pair of course, and they'd give their order, they woul
d
 ignore Arthur. They'd ignore my brother-in-law, it was all my sister. And she used to look so nice behind the - the counter you know. Of course she had to keep a maid you know. But he was never sober you know. And she - the nicest of us and then she got 
married to this old Sam Deeks. Oh - oh my mother nearly - my mother nearly broke her heart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you spend your Sunday any differently? When you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you go morning and night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. My mother usually after I got - a bit older, she would go in the morning, and I'd have her dinner ready when she came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You would stay home in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. To cook it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So you'd go in the afternoon and the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 What about in the weeknight, would you go to anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. Monday - and Thursday. And of course we'd go to - perhaps we'd have a little competitive concert you know, and - Band of Hope. Oh - I didn't used to feel the time long at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, I don't think I did. The biggest interest we took when Queen Victoria died and we all went into mourning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You did say earlier that you spent a lot of your time crocheting and knitting and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes. And sewing. And trying things out you know. And cooking. And if there was a new gadget going - I'd buy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you still sew in the evenings although you were sewing in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
No. We'd never hardly - sew at night you know. But we would do crocheting and then we'd go up to night school where Mary was teaching, a crowd of us would go up there, and - I remember there was a - there was a lady, she was the head of the laund
ry and she had joined. Very nice girl. And of course you know we had nice blouses laundered then, so she said to Mary, my sister, excuse me, she said, who laundered your blouse? And of course I did. And do you know when Mary was getting married you know t
h
at Jane, she was laughing, I was ironing her, you know, her lawan you know and yards of it and embroidery, I've got some of it now, and I was - I was telling Jane, Mary was getting married like the following week and I was ironing her things, and I said, 
oh, I must iron the edging of our Mary's drawers. And that Jane started to laugh you know. Oh dear dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 They were so fancy weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Mm. Oh - yards of stuff. Today - you know, they're simple. And the embroidery, do you know I think - I made 
Nina a - a little cap out of pieces of embroidery, for - she was helping with the Goldowy you know and I thought, oh - it's wicked that we are using these now. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you do anything different when you started work in your spare time, compared with when you were in school? Did you make any new friends?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
New friends? Well - you see, when I was in school my friends were the school friends. Now when we got older our friends were chapel friends, our chapel friends. And I'll tell you who - was o
ne of my biggest friends, and - her sister is alive now and she goes up every other week to see Glyn, to this home, she's - her mother was a niece of Ratcliffe here. And her father - was a mason by trade, but he worked himself up - to be the best architec
t in Merthyr. Fond of the drink again, and poor Mrs -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 There was a lot of drinking then wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh yes, and Mrs Davies was telling me, you see, he was the architect for all the breweries - Giles and Harrod, and all those and they would send
 liquor and things, and she said - I've got enough stuff, she said - to go from our house to Troy de Rue in the gutter. And - oh she went through an or - she had a big family too, and her daughter was one of my biggest friends in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So would you have new friends at all after you left school, or would they be people from the chapel? People you already knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes, we had - we had plenty of friends, we were never short of friends. And - I miss it her you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you bring friends home? Did you take those friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Yes. Well - Friday night - Friday night was an - our at home, I was losing a lot of it because you see, Mary was up in the workroom, and these girls would go up the workroom because my mother wouldn't be bothered, and I'll be downstairs pressing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were doing all that were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
And then she would - well I told you about scorching didn't I? Oh dear, dear, it was hard work. Mind, we worked hard for very little. In those days. Compare it today. They don't look at a pound today. We never saw a pound in - put in our hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you be working in the evening like that pressing a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh no, only on the Friday. See? Unless - I'd have to go downstairs to press you know something - we had one of these b
ig old - a goose they called it, you know the tailors used them. Big - long iron. I don't know what's happened to it, whether - I think Mary must have given it away. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You did all that did you, all the pressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 All the pressing, yes. Well Ma
ry wasn't - I - she wasn't - really as strong as I was you know. And of course she had a lot of mental work you see. 'Cos she - the people - in those days would want your opinion, and you - your advice, and even - bring patterns and material of you to cho
ose you know. Look at my hands, it's due to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You worked hard really didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh dear, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you go out in the evening at all then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh yes. And we'd go on a Thursday - we'd go out to Pontsahn, that's a little countryplace, v
ery pretty. And - we'd - there'd be a nice place there where we could have tea. And perhaps four of us, Mary and I and two others would go. And we'd thoroughly enjoy ourselves, and then we would comeback, walk back you see, it's about - oh four or five mi
les.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 How would you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Walk. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Who would the other two be, girls or boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Girls. Not boys. The boys came later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Much later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - I knew - I knew my husband - but never thought of him as a - as my husband - becaus
e to start with I used to think he's much too tall for me, and - but always nice you know, he would be going now to my - sister's very often up in Dowlas, and - he'd come home - send me home, and - I would tell him all my little troubles. Gwen now - got m
a
rried in Dowlas, my friend that went a nurse you know, and she was Deputy Matron in Liverpool, and - she was married in Dowlas because - she'd been brought up with her - aunt and uncle, nice - he was a deacon in our chapel, well - is this keeping the nois
e
? And - so they got married and - his people came down, very nice people, but I had met them before, because there was a - a bazaar with so many chapels in St George's Hall, Liverpool, and Gwen invited me there you know so I stayed about a fortnight. Beca
u
se she was a - great friend of mine. And - this boy - William John Williams his name is, very nice family - and - lovely from here up, but from there down you could play marbles. And he - he came to the wedding and my mother said to me - she said about th
is William John, and he gave me a - a - he was a timber merchant. And he gave me the - you didn't see that piece of wood that I carved did you, in the middle room? Come and have a look at it. Do you know, about - my mother getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We didn't work out how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Well I should think now - when she - I think - now do you know what I did, we had a big family bible - up the attic, when I left you see because - it really wanted - rebinding but - oh it was a lovel
y old bible, and what I did you see, I don't know what possessed me, all our births were in that, and my mother's marriage, but you know I can't remember dates. And I ripped them out because I thought - well I don't want anyone to see this, you know. Do y
ou know, and we had another bible there with a gold clasp, new, somebody stole that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 We did work out roughly your sister's and brother's birthdays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 There's about - nearly two years between each of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You were born in 1879?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well then Mary was two years older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 So that's about 1877? Jane, 1875. Anne 1873. Ellen 1871. John 1869, sixty-nine or sixty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And then Lisa was the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She was about twelve years older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh she was the eldest you see. She was the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Was she about ten or twelve years older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I should think she'd - she would be twelve. Well now - my mother - I've got no idea of - is a silly thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Your moth
er was about thirty-seven when you were born, and you think your father was about a year older than her, so he'd be about thirty-eight when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Do - do you think my mother would be as old as that now, because there were two after me you se
e. Although mind I - I heard her saying - that - my father's - my father's mother I think - had a child when she was fifty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 If she was thirty-seven when you were born and there was only two years between you and Catherine that would make her thirty-ni
ne, say another two years before Sarah, she'd only be about forty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 YES. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She'd have had the first child about twenty-four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh I'd say she'd have it sooner than that. I'm sure I've heard her saying she was married when she was about
 twenty. And she got married on horseback you know. Not - a posh - you know, form the farm. Nothing posh. But - there was a dress of hers down the cellar you know and we used to look at that and we used to say, this is - this is my mother's - wedding dres
s, and it had strips like of - a mauve silk, you know. Well, well. It's September.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did you have any special friends when you started work, would you make new boy friends? Or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well - yes, of course. Perhaps it would only be for
 a short time you see. You know - perhaps somebody'd bring me back you know from - from the teaparty or something like that, but - of course I - I had - my first sweetheart - he was a minister's son, and he was in an office you know, an office boy, and he
 
- you know those little three cornered - bag of sweets, he'd bring me one of those on a Saturday night see. He was - he was - I couldn't bear the way he used to wipe his nose. And - he - worked himself up to be a solicitor you see. Well he got - we went t
o
 - London now, Mary and Tom - and Martin was going with his - sister, and I was going, and - I think David was there too, and - his sisters would say, look Getta, you walk on with Martin. But you know when they'd go and have a meal, I never wanted to go w
i
th Martin 'cos it's jelly and something like that they'd have and now I'd like a good substantial meal. And - oh and we used to go - on a Sunday morning we'd go down to send them - they lived down the bottom of the town then. Well perhaps you'd know - Emi
ly's daughter she had a very good job here, she was the head of this place where they give relief. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you take these friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. Oh - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Never. My mother never encouraged - did your mother? She never
 encouraged boys, and she'd - she used to call - David - 'cos he was tall, and she'd call Tom because he was an architect. But Catherine now was going - she went you know - she went with her husband, and - when she was a girl, from Band of Hope, and she n
ever went with anyone else. And it's their son now is in this home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would you take girlfriends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Would your mother expect ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 But not boys. They - they would never come - there was one boy, he was very friendly with
 - my husband, he was a grocer too, good looking tall boy, and he was going with our little organist, Edith Matthews, and going very seriously, well now he was very friendly with David, and - he was living in Merthyr you see well - as David lived in Dowla
s
 so he'd come and send me home, and he'd start talking - I'd start talking to him about Edith because I felt oh - you know - I felt a bit awkward because she had died, and - he came to our house and inside the passage you know the - behind the door like, 
my godfather, he started - he started kissing me and he was shaking like a leaf. I was frightened, I got - I'd never been with a boy like this before. And poor old - poor old Griff.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Bother with him after that night did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. I - I was never s
o frightened in all my life. Well - I said - I said - I said to my sister, it's no wonder poor Eidith is dead, I said, he's like a shivery shake. And she - and she was so dainty you know, she was - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 You weren't very old then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No. 
She was such a dainty little thing you know, and for - well - good lord I don't know, it's enough to frighten her, it's no wonder she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well she knew that I used to go up to - 
Catherine got married you see before Mary and I because there was a house going with the job, he was a stores manager you see up there and then he got on - to do clerical, he was very clever - Glyn - Glyn's father, and - he was David Davies you see, so th
en I had to call David, Welsh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did your mother like to know where you were when you went out with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 No, she was never fussy like that you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Did she expect you to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well no, if I'd go up to
 Dowlas, you see, I'd - perhaps it would be - twelve o'clock when we'd be walking, there'd be no buses. And we'd have to walk down. But oh I was as safe - with Griff and with - with David, until that one night, I never told David.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 She didn't worry about you being out or anything like that, you didn't have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 
Oh no, no. No. But I'll tell you I used to feel very awkward - when - when David started you know being friendly really friendly, he'd come in you know and my mother 
had gone to bed you see, and - I used to feel - most awkward because I knew that she didn't like it, that he was coming in you know, and I had to tell him he could only stay for a very short time, I used to tell him to go you know. But she liked him, he w
as - well she - you - you couldn't help liking him, he was - such a sane man you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Where would you go with your friends when you were working, where would you go of an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Oh we'd go perhaps - we'd walk up and down town you know. And - 
well if we were not in chapel - perhaps we'd go for a country walk, because there were lovely country walks round Merthyr, but it - it's all been built on now you know. You see, we had plenty of open spaces. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 When your daughter was born I think we worked it out as 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303695 MD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 Well Nina would know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6557306 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11102\charrsid7633169 And it was 1915 you got married? Tudor your son was born 1920?
